2129 namespace {
2130 void Generate_ContinueToBuiltinHelper(MacroAssembler* masm,
2131  bool javascript_builtin,
2132  bool with_result) {
2133  const RegisterConfiguration* config(RegisterConfiguration::Default());
2134  int allocatable_register_count = config->num_allocatable_general_registers();
2135  int frame_size = BuiltinContinuationFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeFromFp +
2136  (allocatable_register_count +
2137  BuiltinContinuationFrameConstants::PaddingSlotCount(
2138  allocatable_register_count)) *
2139  kSystemPointerSize;
2140 
2141  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm);
2142  Register scratch = temps.AcquireX(); // Temp register is not allocatable.
2143 
2144  // Set up frame pointer.
2145  __ Add(fp, sp, frame_size);
2146 
2147  if (with_result) {
2148  if (javascript_builtin) {
2149  __ mov(scratch, x0);
2150  } else {
2151  // Overwrite the hole inserted by the deoptimizer with the return value
2152  // from the LAZY deopt point.
2153  __ Str(x0, MemOperand(
2154  fp, BuiltinContinuationFrameConstants::kCallerSPOffset));
2155  }
2156  }
2157 
2158  // Restore registers in pairs.
2159  int offset = -BuiltinContinuationFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeFromFp -
2160  allocatable_register_count * kSystemPointerSize;
2161  for (int i = allocatable_register_count - 1; i > 0; i -= 2) {
2162  int code1 = config->GetAllocatableGeneralCode(i);
2163  int code2 = config->GetAllocatableGeneralCode(i - 1);
2164  Register reg1 = Register::from_code(code1);
2165  Register reg2 = Register::from_code(code2);
2166  __ Ldp(reg1, reg2, MemOperand(fp, offset));
2167  offset += 2 * kSystemPointerSize;
2168  }
2169 
2170  // Restore first register separately, if number of registers is odd.
2171  if (allocatable_register_count % 2 != 0) {
2172  int code = config->GetAllocatableGeneralCode(0);
2173  __ Ldr(Register::from_code(code), MemOperand(fp, offset));
2174  }
2175 
2176  if (javascript_builtin) __ SmiUntag(kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister);
2177 
2178  if (javascript_builtin && with_result) {
2179  // Overwrite the hole inserted by the deoptimizer with the return value from
2180  // the LAZY deopt point. x0 contains the arguments count, the return value
2181  // from LAZY is always the last argument.
2182  constexpr int return_offset =
2183  BuiltinContinuationFrameConstants::kCallerSPOffset /
2184  kSystemPointerSize -
2185  kJSArgcReceiverSlots;
2186  __ add(x0, x0, return_offset);
2187  __ Str(scratch, MemOperand(fp, x0, LSL, kSystemPointerSizeLog2));
2188  // Recover argument count.
2189  __ sub(x0, x0, return_offset);
2190  }
2191 
2192  // Load builtin index (stored as a Smi) and use it to get the builtin start
2193  // address from the builtins table.
2194  Register builtin = scratch;
2195  __ Ldr(
2196  builtin,
2197  MemOperand(fp, BuiltinContinuationFrameConstants::kBuiltinIndexOffset));
2198 
2199  // Restore fp, lr.
2200  __ Mov(sp, fp);
2201  __ Pop<MacroAssembler::kAuthLR>(fp, lr);
2202 
2203  __ LoadEntryFromBuiltinIndex(builtin, builtin);
2204  __ Jump(builtin);
2205 }

2264 
2265 void OnStackReplacement(MacroAssembler* masm, OsrSourceTier source,
2266  Register maybe_target_code,
2267  Register expected_param_count) {
2268  Label jump_to_optimized_code;
2269  {
2270  // If maybe_target_code is not null, no need to call into runtime. A
2271  // precondition here is: if maybe_target_code is an InstructionStream
2272  // object, it must NOT be marked_for_deoptimization (callers must ensure
2273  // this).
2274  __ CompareTaggedAndBranch(maybe_target_code, Smi::zero(), ne,
2275  &jump_to_optimized_code);
2276  }
2277 
2278  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(masm);
2279  {
2280  FrameScope scope(masm, StackFrame::INTERNAL);
2281  __ Push(expected_param_count, padreg);
2282  __ CallRuntime(Runtime::kCompileOptimizedOSR);
2283  DCHECK_EQ(maybe_target_code, x0);
2284  __ Pop(padreg, expected_param_count);
2285  }
2286 
2287  // If the code object is null, just return to the caller.
2288  __ CompareTaggedAndBranch(maybe_target_code, Smi::zero(), ne,
2289  &jump_to_optimized_code);
2290  __ Ret();
2291 
2292  __ Bind(&jump_to_optimized_code);
2293 
2294  const Register scratch(x2);
2295  CHECK(!AreAliased(maybe_target_code, expected_param_count, scratch));
2296 
2297  // OSR entry tracing.
2298  {
2299  Label next;
2300  __ Mov(scratch, ExternalReference::address_of_log_or_trace_osr());
2301  __ Ldrsb(scratch, MemOperand(scratch));
2302  __ Tst(scratch, 0xFF); // Mask to the LSB.
2303  __ B(eq, &next);
2304 
2305  {
2306  FrameScope scope(masm, StackFrame::INTERNAL);
2307  // Preserve arguments.
2308  __ Push(maybe_target_code, expected_param_count);
2309  __ CallRuntime(Runtime::kLogOrTraceOptimizedOSREntry, 0);
2310  __ Pop(expected_param_count, maybe_target_code);
2311  }
2312 
2313  __ Bind(&next);
2314  }
2315 
2316  if (source == OsrSourceTier::kInterpreter) {
2317  // Drop the handler frame that is be sitting on top of the actual
2318  // JavaScript frame. This is the case then OSR is triggered from bytecode.
2319  __ LeaveFrame(StackFrame::STUB);
2320  }
2321 
2322  // Check we are actually jumping to an OSR code object. This among other
2323  // things ensures that the object contains deoptimization data below.
2324  __ Ldr(scratch.W(),
2325  FieldMemOperand(maybe_target_code, Code::kOsrOffsetOffset));
2326  __ Cmp(scratch.W(), BytecodeOffset::None().ToInt());
2327  __ SbxCheck(Condition::kNotEqual, AbortReason::kExpectedOsrCode);
2328 
2329  // Check the target has a matching parameter count. This ensures that the OSR
2330  // code will correctly tear down our frame when leaving.
2331  __ Ldrh(scratch.W(),
2332  FieldMemOperand(maybe_target_code, Code::kParameterCountOffset));
2333  __ SmiUntag(expected_param_count);
2334  __ Cmp(scratch.W(), expected_param_count.W());
2335  __ SbxCheck(Condition::kEqual, AbortReason::kOsrUnexpectedStackSize);
2336 
2337  // Load deoptimization data from the code object.
2338  // <deopt_data> = <code>[#deoptimization_data_offset]
2339  __ LoadProtectedPointerField(
2340  scratch,
2341  FieldMemOperand(maybe_target_code,
2342  Code::kDeoptimizationDataOrInterpreterDataOffset));
2343 
2344  // Load the OSR entrypoint offset from the deoptimization data.
2345  // <osr_offset> = <deopt_data>[#header_size + #osr_pc_offset]
2346  __ SmiUntagField(
2347  scratch,
2348  FieldMemOperand(scratch, TrustedFixedArray::OffsetOfElementAt(
2349  DeoptimizationData::kOsrPcOffsetIndex)));
2350 
2351  __ LoadCodeInstructionStart(maybe_target_code, maybe_target_code,
2352  kJSEntrypointTag);
2353 
2354  // Compute the target address = code_entry + osr_offset
2355  // <entry_addr> = <code_entry> + <osr_offset>
2356  Generate_OSREntry(masm, maybe_target_code, scratch);
2357 }

2410 // static
2411 void Builtins::Generate_FunctionPrototypeApply(MacroAssembler* masm) {
2412  // ----------- S t a t e -------------
2413  // -- x0 : argc
2414  // -- sp[0] : receiver
2415  // -- sp[8] : thisArg (if argc >= 1)
2416  // -- sp[16] : argArray (if argc == 2)
2417  // -----------------------------------
2418 
2419  ASM_LOCATION("Builtins::Generate_FunctionPrototypeApply");
2420 
2421  Register argc = x0;
2422  Register receiver = x1;
2423  Register arg_array = x2;
2424  Register this_arg = x3;
2425  Register undefined_value = x4;
2426  Register null_value = x5;
2427 
2428  __ LoadRoot(undefined_value, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
2429  __ LoadRoot(null_value, RootIndex::kNullValue);
2430 
2431  // 1. Load receiver into x1, argArray into x2 (if present), remove all
2432  // arguments from the stack (including the receiver), and push thisArg (if
2433  // present) instead.
2434  {
2435  Label done;
2436  __ Mov(this_arg, undefined_value);
2437  __ Mov(arg_array, undefined_value);
2438  __ Peek(receiver, 0);
2439  __ Cmp(argc, Immediate(JSParameterCount(1)));
2440  __ B(lt, &done);
2441  __ Peek(this_arg, kSystemPointerSize);
2442  __ B(eq, &done);
2443  __ Peek(arg_array, 2 * kSystemPointerSize);
2444  __ bind(&done);
2445  }
2446  __ DropArguments(argc);
2447  __ PushArgument(this_arg);
2448 
2449  // ----------- S t a t e -------------
2450  // -- x2 : argArray
2451  // -- x1 : receiver
2452  // -- sp[0] : thisArg
2453  // -----------------------------------
2454 
2455  // 2. We don't need to check explicitly for callable receiver here,
2456  // since that's the first thing the Call/CallWithArrayLike builtins
2457  // will do.
2458 
2459  // 3. Tail call with no arguments if argArray is null or undefined.
2460  Label no_arguments;
2461  __ CmpTagged(arg_array, null_value);
2462  __ CcmpTagged(arg_array, undefined_value, ZFlag, ne);
2463  __ B(eq, &no_arguments);
2464 
2465  // 4a. Apply the receiver to the given argArray.
2466  __ TailCallBuiltin(Builtin::kCallWithArrayLike);
2467 
2468  // 4b. The argArray is either null or undefined, so we tail call without any
2469  // arguments to the receiver.
2470  __ Bind(&no_arguments);
2471  {
2472  __ Mov(x0, JSParameterCount(0));
2473  DCHECK_EQ(receiver, x1);
2474  __ TailCallBuiltin(Builtins::Call());
2475  }
2476 }

2478 // static
2479 void Builtins::Generate_FunctionPrototypeCall(MacroAssembler* masm) {
2480  Register argc = x0;
2481  Register function = x1;
2482 
2483  ASM_LOCATION("Builtins::Generate_FunctionPrototypeCall");
2484 
2485  // 1. Get the callable to call (passed as receiver) from the stack.
2486  __ Peek(function, __ ReceiverOperand());
2487 
2488  // 2. Handle case with no arguments.
2489  {
2490  Label non_zero;
2491  Register scratch = x10;
2492  __ Cmp(argc, JSParameterCount(0));
2493  __ B(gt, &non_zero);
2494  __ LoadRoot(scratch, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
2495  // Overwrite receiver with undefined, which will be the new receiver.
2496  // We do not need to overwrite the padding slot above it with anything.
2497  __ Poke(scratch, 0);
2498  // Call function. The argument count is already zero.
2499  __ TailCallBuiltin(Builtins::Call());
2500  __ Bind(&non_zero);
2501  }
2502 
2503  Label arguments_ready;
2504  // 3. Shift arguments. It depends if the arguments is even or odd.
2505  // That is if padding exists or not.
2506  {
2507  Label even;
2508  Register copy_from = x10;
2509  Register copy_to = x11;
2510  Register count = x12;
2511  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm);
2512  Register argc_without_receiver = temps.AcquireX();
2513  __ Sub(argc_without_receiver, argc, kJSArgcReceiverSlots);
2514 
2515  // CopyDoubleWords changes the count argument.
2516  __ Mov(count, argc_without_receiver);
2517  __ Tbz(argc_without_receiver, 0, &even);
2518 
2519  // Shift arguments one slot down on the stack (overwriting the original
2520  // receiver).
2521  __ SlotAddress(copy_from, 1);
2522  __ Sub(copy_to, copy_from, kSystemPointerSize);
2523  __ CopyDoubleWords(copy_to, copy_from, count);
2524  // Overwrite the duplicated remaining last argument.
2525  __ Poke(padreg, Operand(argc_without_receiver, LSL, kXRegSizeLog2));
2526  __ B(&arguments_ready);
2527 
2528  // Copy arguments one slot higher in memory, overwriting the original
2529  // receiver and padding.
2530  __ Bind(&even);
2531  __ SlotAddress(copy_from, count);
2532  __ Add(copy_to, copy_from, kSystemPointerSize);
2533  __ CopyDoubleWords(copy_to, copy_from, count,
2534  MacroAssembler::kSrcLessThanDst);
2535  __ Drop(2);
2536  }
2537 
2538  // 5. Adjust argument count to make the original first argument the new
2539  // receiver and call the callable.
2540  __ Bind(&arguments_ready);
2541  __ Sub(argc, argc, 1);
2542  __ TailCallBuiltin(Builtins::Call());
2543 }

2665 // Prepares the stack for copying the varargs. First we claim the necessary
2666 // slots, taking care of potential padding. Then we copy the existing arguments
2667 // one slot up or one slot down, as needed.
2668 void Generate_PrepareForCopyingVarargs(MacroAssembler* masm, Register argc,
2669  Register len) {
2670  Label exit, even, init;
2671  Register slots_to_copy = x10;
2672  Register slots_to_claim = x12;
2673 
2674  __ Mov(slots_to_copy, argc);
2675  __ Mov(slots_to_claim, len);
2676  __ Tbz(slots_to_claim, 0, &even);
2677 
2678  // Claim space we need. If argc (without receiver) is even, slots_to_claim =
2679  // len + 1, as we need one extra padding slot. If argc (without receiver) is
2680  // odd, we know that the original arguments will have a padding slot we can
2681  // reuse (since len is odd), so slots_to_claim = len - 1.
2682  {
2683  Register scratch = x11;
2684  __ Add(slots_to_claim, len, 1);
2685  __ And(scratch, argc, 1);
2686  __ Sub(slots_to_claim, slots_to_claim, Operand(scratch, LSL, 1));
2687  }
2688 
2689  __ Bind(&even);
2690  __ Cbz(slots_to_claim, &exit);
2691  __ Claim(slots_to_claim);
2692  // An alignment slot may have been allocated above. If the number of stack
2693  // parameters is 0, the we have to initialize the alignment slot.
2694  __ Cbz(slots_to_copy, &init);
2695 
2696  // Move the arguments already in the stack including the receiver.
2697  {
2698  Register src = x11;
2699  Register dst = x12;
2700  __ SlotAddress(src, slots_to_claim);
2701  __ SlotAddress(dst, 0);
2702  __ CopyDoubleWords(dst, src, slots_to_copy);
2703  __ jmp(&exit);
2704  }
2705  // Initialize the alignment slot with a meaningful value. This is only
2706  // necessary if slots_to_copy is 0, because otherwise the alignment slot
2707  // already contains a valid value. In case slots_to_copy is even, then the
2708  // alignment slot contains the last parameter passed over the stack. In case
2709  // slots_to_copy is odd, then the alignment slot is that alignment slot when
2710  // CallVarArgs (or similar) was called, and already got initialized for that
2711  // call.
2712  {
2713  __ Bind(&init);
2714  // This code here is only reached when the number of stack parameters is 0.
2715  // In that case we have to initialize the alignment slot if there is one.
2716  __ Tbz(len, 0, &exit);
2717  __ Str(xzr, MemOperand(sp, len, LSL, kSystemPointerSizeLog2));
2718  }
2719  __ Bind(&exit);
2720 }

2724 // static
2725 // TODO(v8:11615): Observe Code::kMaxArguments in CallOrConstructVarargs
2726 void Builtins::Generate_CallOrConstructVarargs(MacroAssembler* masm,
2727  Builtin target_builtin) {
2728  // ----------- S t a t e -------------
2729  // -- x1 : target
2730  // -- x0 : number of parameters on the stack
2731  // -- x2 : arguments list (a FixedArray)
2732  // -- x4 : len (number of elements to push from args)
2733  // -- x3 : new.target (for [[Construct]])
2734  // -----------------------------------
2735  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
2736  // Allow x2 to be a FixedArray, or a FixedDoubleArray if x4 == 0.
2737  Label ok, fail;
2738  __ AssertNotSmi(x2, AbortReason::kOperandIsNotAFixedArray);
2739  __ LoadTaggedField(x10, FieldMemOperand(x2, HeapObject::kMapOffset));
2740  __ Ldrh(x13, FieldMemOperand(x10, Map::kInstanceTypeOffset));
2741  __ Cmp(x13, FIXED_ARRAY_TYPE);
2742  __ B(eq, &ok);
2743  __ Cmp(x13, FIXED_DOUBLE_ARRAY_TYPE);
2744  __ B(ne, &fail);
2745  __ Cmp(x4, 0);
2746  __ B(eq, &ok);
2747  // Fall through.
2748  __ bind(&fail);
2749  __ Abort(AbortReason::kOperandIsNotAFixedArray);
2750 
2751  __ bind(&ok);
2752  }
2753 
2754  Register arguments_list = x2;
2755  Register argc = x0;
2756  Register len = x4;
2757 
2758  Label stack_overflow;
2759  __ StackOverflowCheck(len, &stack_overflow);
2760 
2761  // Skip argument setup if we don't need to push any varargs.
2762  Label done;
2763  __ Cbz(len, &done);
2764 
2765  Generate_PrepareForCopyingVarargs(masm, argc, len);
2766 
2767  // Push varargs.
2768  {
2769  Label loop;
2770  Register src = x10;
2771  Register undefined_value = x12;
2772  Register scratch = x13;
2773  __ Add(src, arguments_list,
2774  OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(FixedArray) - kHeapObjectTag);
2775 #if !V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
2776  // We do not use the CompareRoot macro without static roots as it would do a
2777  // LoadRoot behind the scenes and we want to avoid that in a loop.
2778  Register the_hole_value = x11;
2779  __ LoadTaggedRoot(the_hole_value, RootIndex::kTheHoleValue);
2780 #endif // !V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
2781  __ LoadRoot(undefined_value, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
2782  // TODO(all): Consider using Ldp and Stp.
2783  Register dst = x16;
2784  __ SlotAddress(dst, argc);
2785  __ Add(argc, argc, len); // Update new argc.
2786  __ Bind(&loop);
2787  __ Sub(len, len, 1);
2788  __ LoadTaggedField(scratch, MemOperand(src, kTaggedSize, PostIndex));
2789 #if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
2790  __ CompareRoot(scratch, RootIndex::kTheHoleValue);
2791 #else
2792  __ CmpTagged(scratch, the_hole_value);
2793 #endif
2794  __ Csel(scratch, scratch, undefined_value, ne);
2795  __ Str(scratch, MemOperand(dst, kSystemPointerSize, PostIndex));
2796  __ Cbnz(len, &loop);
2797  }
2798  __ Bind(&done);
2799  // Tail-call to the actual Call or Construct builtin.
2800  __ TailCallBuiltin(target_builtin);
2801 
2802  __ bind(&stack_overflow);
2803  __ TailCallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowStackOverflow);
2804 }

2806 // static
2807 void Builtins::Generate_CallOrConstructForwardVarargs(MacroAssembler* masm,
2808  CallOrConstructMode mode,
2809  Builtin target_builtin) {
2810  // ----------- S t a t e -------------
2811  // -- x0 : the number of arguments
2812  // -- x3 : the new.target (for [[Construct]] calls)
2813  // -- x1 : the target to call (can be any Object)
2814  // -- x2 : start index (to support rest parameters)
2815  // -----------------------------------
2816 
2817  Register argc = x0;
2818  Register start_index = x2;
2819 
2820  // Check if new.target has a [[Construct]] internal method.
2821  if (mode == CallOrConstructMode::kConstruct) {
2822  Label new_target_constructor, new_target_not_constructor;
2823  __ JumpIfSmi(x3, &new_target_not_constructor);
2824  __ LoadTaggedField(x5, FieldMemOperand(x3, HeapObject::kMapOffset));
2825  __ Ldrb(x5, FieldMemOperand(x5, Map::kBitFieldOffset));
2826  __ TestAndBranchIfAnySet(x5, Map::Bits1::IsConstructorBit::kMask,
2827  &new_target_constructor);
2828  __ Bind(&new_target_not_constructor);
2829  {
2830  FrameScope scope(masm, StackFrame::MANUAL);
2831  __ EnterFrame(StackFrame::INTERNAL);
2832  __ PushArgument(x3);
2833  __ CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowNotConstructor);
2834  __ Unreachable();
2835  }
2836  __ Bind(&new_target_constructor);
2837  }
2838 
2839  Register len = x6;
2840  Label stack_done, stack_overflow;
2841  __ Ldr(len, MemOperand(fp, StandardFrameConstants::kArgCOffset));
2842  __ Subs(len, len, kJSArgcReceiverSlots);
2843  __ Subs(len, len, start_index);
2844  __ B(le, &stack_done);
2845  // Check for stack overflow.
2846  __ StackOverflowCheck(len, &stack_overflow);
2847 
2848  Generate_PrepareForCopyingVarargs(masm, argc, len);
2849 
2850  // Push varargs.
2851  {
2852  Register args_fp = x5;
2853  Register dst = x13;
2854  // Point to the fist argument to copy from (skipping receiver).
2855  __ Add(args_fp, fp,
2856  CommonFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeAboveFp + kSystemPointerSize);
2857  __ lsl(start_index, start_index, kSystemPointerSizeLog2);
2858  __ Add(args_fp, args_fp, start_index);
2859  // Point to the position to copy to.
2860  __ SlotAddress(dst, argc);
2861  // Update total number of arguments.
2862  __ Add(argc, argc, len);
2863  __ CopyDoubleWords(dst, args_fp, len);
2864  }
2865 
2866  __ Bind(&stack_done);
2867  // Tail-call to the actual Call or Construct builtin.
2868  __ TailCallBuiltin(target_builtin);
2869 
2870  __ Bind(&stack_overflow);
2871  __ TailCallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowStackOverflow);
2872 }

2874 // static
2875 void Builtins::Generate_CallFunction(MacroAssembler* masm,
2876  ConvertReceiverMode mode) {
2877  ASM_LOCATION("Builtins::Generate_CallFunction");
2878  // ----------- S t a t e -------------
2879  // -- x0 : the number of arguments
2880  // -- x1 : the function to call (checked to be a JSFunction)
2881  // -----------------------------------
2882  __ AssertCallableFunction(x1);
2883 
2884  __ LoadTaggedField(
2885  x2, FieldMemOperand(x1, JSFunction::kSharedFunctionInfoOffset));
2886 
2887  // Enter the context of the function; ToObject has to run in the function
2888  // context, and we also need to take the global proxy from the function
2889  // context in case of conversion.
2890  __ LoadTaggedField(cp, FieldMemOperand(x1, JSFunction::kContextOffset));
2891  // We need to convert the receiver for non-native sloppy mode functions.
2892  Label done_convert;
2893  __ Ldr(w3, FieldMemOperand(x2, SharedFunctionInfo::kFlagsOffset));
2894  __ TestAndBranchIfAnySet(w3,
2895  SharedFunctionInfo::IsNativeBit::kMask |
2896  SharedFunctionInfo::IsStrictBit::kMask,
2897  &done_convert);
2898  {
2899  // ----------- S t a t e -------------
2900  // -- x0 : the number of arguments
2901  // -- x1 : the function to call (checked to be a JSFunction)
2902  // -- x2 : the shared function info.
2903  // -- cp : the function context.
2904  // -----------------------------------
2905 
2906  if (mode == ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined) {
2907  // Patch receiver to global proxy.
2908  __ LoadGlobalProxy(x3);
2909  } else {
2910  Label convert_to_object, convert_receiver;
2911  __ Peek(x3, __ ReceiverOperand());
2912  __ JumpIfSmi(x3, &convert_to_object);
2913  __ JumpIfJSAnyIsNotPrimitive(x3, x4, &done_convert);
2914  if (mode != ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined) {
2915  Label convert_global_proxy;
2916  __ JumpIfRoot(x3, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue, &convert_global_proxy);
2917  __ JumpIfNotRoot(x3, RootIndex::kNullValue, &convert_to_object);
2918  __ Bind(&convert_global_proxy);
2919  {
2920  // Patch receiver to global proxy.
2921  __ LoadGlobalProxy(x3);
2922  }
2923  __ B(&convert_receiver);
2924  }
2925  __ Bind(&convert_to_object);
2926  {
2927  // Convert receiver using ToObject.
2928  // TODO(bmeurer): Inline the allocation here to avoid building the frame
2929  // in the fast case? (fall back to AllocateInNewSpace?)
2930  FrameScope scope(masm, StackFrame::INTERNAL);
2931  __ SmiTag(x0);
2932  __ Push(padreg, x0, x1, cp);
2933  __ Mov(x0, x3);
2934  __ CallBuiltin(Builtin::kToObject);
2935  __ Mov(x3, x0);
2936  __ Pop(cp, x1, x0, padreg);
2937  __ SmiUntag(x0);
2938  }
2939  __ LoadTaggedField(
2940  x2, FieldMemOperand(x1, JSFunction::kSharedFunctionInfoOffset));
2941  __ Bind(&convert_receiver);
2942  }
2943  __ Poke(x3, __ ReceiverOperand());
2944  }
2945  __ Bind(&done_convert);
2946 
2947  // ----------- S t a t e -------------
2948  // -- x0 : the number of arguments
2949  // -- x1 : the function to call (checked to be a JSFunction)
2950  // -- x2 : the shared function info.
2951  // -- cp : the function context.
2952  // -----------------------------------
2953 
2954 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
2955  __ InvokeFunctionCode(x1, no_reg, x0, InvokeType::kJump);
2956 #else
2957  __ Ldrh(x2,
2958  FieldMemOperand(x2, SharedFunctionInfo::kFormalParameterCountOffset));
2959  __ InvokeFunctionCode(x1, no_reg, x2, x0, InvokeType::kJump);
2960 #endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
2961 }

2965 void Generate_PushBoundArguments(MacroAssembler* masm) {
2966  // ----------- S t a t e -------------
2967  // -- x0 : the number of arguments
2968  // -- x1 : target (checked to be a JSBoundFunction)
2969  // -- x3 : new.target (only in case of [[Construct]])
2970  // -----------------------------------
2971 
2972  Register bound_argc = x4;
2973  Register bound_argv = x2;
2974 
2975  // Load [[BoundArguments]] into x2 and length of that into x4.
2976  Label no_bound_arguments;
2977  __ LoadTaggedField(
2978  bound_argv, FieldMemOperand(x1, JSBoundFunction::kBoundArgumentsOffset));
2979  __ SmiUntagField(bound_argc,
2980  FieldMemOperand(bound_argv, offsetof(FixedArray, length_)));
2981  __ Cbz(bound_argc, &no_bound_arguments);
2982  {
2983  // ----------- S t a t e -------------
2984  // -- x0 : the number of arguments
2985  // -- x1 : target (checked to be a JSBoundFunction)
2986  // -- x2 : the [[BoundArguments]] (implemented as FixedArray)
2987  // -- x3 : new.target (only in case of [[Construct]])
2988  // -- x4 : the number of [[BoundArguments]]
2989  // -----------------------------------
2990 
2991  Register argc = x0;
2992 
2993  // Check for stack overflow.
2994  {
2995  // Check the stack for overflow. We are not trying to catch interruptions
2996  // (i.e. debug break and preemption) here, so check the "real stack
2997  // limit".
2998  Label done;
2999  __ LoadStackLimit(x10, StackLimitKind::kRealStackLimit);
3000  // Make x10 the space we have left. The stack might already be overflowed
3001  // here which will cause x10 to become negative.
3002  __ Sub(x10, sp, x10);
3003  // Check if the arguments will overflow the stack.
3004  __ Cmp(x10, Operand(bound_argc, LSL, kSystemPointerSizeLog2));
3005  __ B(gt, &done);
3006  __ TailCallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowStackOverflow);
3007  __ Bind(&done);
3008  }
3009 
3010  Label copy_bound_args;
3011  Register total_argc = x15;
3012  Register slots_to_claim = x12;
3013  Register scratch = x10;
3014  Register receiver = x14;
3015 
3016  __ Sub(argc, argc, kJSArgcReceiverSlots);
3017  __ Add(total_argc, argc, bound_argc);
3018  __ Peek(receiver, 0);
3019 
3020  // Round up slots_to_claim to an even number if it is odd.
3021  __ Add(slots_to_claim, bound_argc, 1);
3022  __ Bic(slots_to_claim, slots_to_claim, 1);
3023  __ Claim(slots_to_claim, kSystemPointerSize);
3024 
3025  __ Tbz(bound_argc, 0, &copy_bound_args);
3026  {
3027  Label argc_even;
3028  __ Tbz(argc, 0, &argc_even);
3029  // Arguments count is odd (with the receiver it's even), so there's no
3030  // alignment padding above the arguments and we have to "add" it. We
3031  // claimed bound_argc + 1, since it is odd and it was rounded up. +1 here
3032  // is for stack alignment padding.
3033  // 1. Shift args one slot down.
3034  {
3035  Register copy_from = x11;
3036  Register copy_to = x12;
3037  __ SlotAddress(copy_to, slots_to_claim);
3038  __ Add(copy_from, copy_to, kSystemPointerSize);
3039  __ CopyDoubleWords(copy_to, copy_from, argc);
3040  }
3041  // 2. Write a padding in the last slot.
3042  __ Add(scratch, total_argc, 1);
3043  __ Str(padreg, MemOperand(sp, scratch, LSL, kSystemPointerSizeLog2));
3044  __ B(&copy_bound_args);
3045 
3046  __ Bind(&argc_even);
3047  // Arguments count is even (with the receiver it's odd), so there's an
3048  // alignment padding above the arguments and we can reuse it. We need to
3049  // claim bound_argc - 1, but we claimed bound_argc + 1, since it is odd
3050  // and it was rounded up.
3051  // 1. Drop 2.
3052  __ Drop(2);
3053  // 2. Shift args one slot up.
3054  {
3055  Register copy_from = x11;
3056  Register copy_to = x12;
3057  __ SlotAddress(copy_to, total_argc);
3058  __ Sub(copy_from, copy_to, kSystemPointerSize);
3059  __ CopyDoubleWords(copy_to, copy_from, argc,
3060  MacroAssembler::kSrcLessThanDst);
3061  }
3062  }
3063 
3064  // If bound_argc is even, there is no alignment massage to do, and we have
3065  // already claimed the correct number of slots (bound_argc).
3066  __ Bind(&copy_bound_args);
3067 
3068  // Copy the receiver back.
3069  __ Poke(receiver, 0);
3070  // Copy [[BoundArguments]] to the stack (below the receiver).
3071  {
3072  Label loop;
3073  Register counter = bound_argc;
3074  Register copy_to = x12;
3075  __ Add(bound_argv, bound_argv,
3076  OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(FixedArray) - kHeapObjectTag);
3077  __ SlotAddress(copy_to, 1);
3078  __ Bind(&loop);
3079  __ Sub(counter, counter, 1);
3080  __ LoadTaggedField(scratch,
3081  MemOperand(bound_argv, kTaggedSize, PostIndex));
3082  __ Str(scratch, MemOperand(copy_to, kSystemPointerSize, PostIndex));
3083  __ Cbnz(counter, &loop);
3084  }
3085  // Update argc.
3086  __ Add(argc, total_argc, kJSArgcReceiverSlots);
3087  }
3088  __ Bind(&no_bound_arguments);
3089 }

3115 // static
3116 void Builtins::Generate_Call(MacroAssembler* masm, ConvertReceiverMode mode) {
3117  // ----------- S t a t e -------------
3118  // -- x0 : the number of arguments
3119  // -- x1 : the target to call (can be any Object).
3120  // -----------------------------------
3121  Register target = x1;
3122  Register map = x4;
3123  Register instance_type = x5;
3124  DCHECK(!AreAliased(x0, target, map, instance_type));
3125 
3126  Label non_callable, class_constructor;
3127  __ JumpIfSmi(target, &non_callable);
3128  __ LoadMap(map, target);
3129  __ CompareInstanceTypeRange(map, instance_type,
3130  FIRST_CALLABLE_JS_FUNCTION_TYPE,
3131  LAST_CALLABLE_JS_FUNCTION_TYPE);
3132  __ TailCallBuiltin(Builtins::CallFunction(mode), ls);
3133  __ Cmp(instance_type, JS_BOUND_FUNCTION_TYPE);
3134  __ TailCallBuiltin(Builtin::kCallBoundFunction, eq);
3135 
3136  // Check if target has a [[Call]] internal method.
3137  {
3138  Register flags = x4;
3139  __ Ldrb(flags, FieldMemOperand(map, Map::kBitFieldOffset));
3140  map = no_reg;
3141  __ TestAndBranchIfAllClear(flags, Map::Bits1::IsCallableBit::kMask,
3142  &non_callable);
3143  }
3144 
3145  // Check if target is a proxy and call CallProxy external builtin
3146  __ Cmp(instance_type, JS_PROXY_TYPE);
3147  __ TailCallBuiltin(Builtin::kCallProxy, eq);
3148 
3149  // Check if target is a wrapped function and call CallWrappedFunction external
3150  // builtin
3151  __ Cmp(instance_type, JS_WRAPPED_FUNCTION_TYPE);
3152  __ TailCallBuiltin(Builtin::kCallWrappedFunction, eq);
3153 
3154  // ES6 section 9.2.1 [[Call]] ( thisArgument, argumentsList)
3155  // Check that the function is not a "classConstructor".
3156  __ Cmp(instance_type, JS_CLASS_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE);
3157  __ B(eq, &class_constructor);
3158 
3159  // 2. Call to something else, which might have a [[Call]] internal method (if
3160  // not we raise an exception).
3161  // Overwrite the original receiver with the (original) target.
3162  __ Poke(target, __ ReceiverOperand());
3163 
3164  // Let the "call_as_function_delegate" take care of the rest.
3165  __ LoadNativeContextSlot(target, Context::CALL_AS_FUNCTION_DELEGATE_INDEX);
3166  __ TailCallBuiltin(
3167  Builtins::CallFunction(ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined));
3168 
3169  // 3. Call to something that is not callable.
3170  __ bind(&non_callable);
3171  {
3172  FrameScope scope(masm, StackFrame::INTERNAL);
3173  __ PushArgument(target);
3174  __ CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowCalledNonCallable);
3175  __ Unreachable();
3176  }
3177 
3178  // 4. The function is a "classConstructor", need to raise an exception.
3179  __ bind(&class_constructor);
3180  {
3181  FrameScope frame(masm, StackFrame::INTERNAL);
3182  __ PushArgument(target);
3183  __ CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowConstructorNonCallableError);
3184  __ Unreachable();
3185  }
3186 }

3307 // Compute register lists for parameters to be saved. We save all parameter

3314  saved_gp_regs.set(gp_param_reg);

3339 // When entering this builtin, we have just created a Wasm stack frame:
3340 //
3341 // [ Wasm instance data ] <-- sp
3342 // [ WASM frame marker ]
3343 // [ saved fp ] <-- fp
3344 //
3345 // Due to stack alignment restrictions, this builtin adds the feedback vector
3346 // plus a filler to the stack. The stack pointer will be
3347 // moved an appropriate distance by {PatchPrepareStackFrame}.
3348 //
3349 // [ (unused) ] <-- sp
3350 // [ feedback vector ]
3351 // [ Wasm instance data ]
3352 // [ WASM frame marker ]
3353 // [ saved fp ] <-- fp
3354 void Builtins::Generate_WasmLiftoffFrameSetup(MacroAssembler* masm) {
3355  Register func_index = wasm::kLiftoffFrameSetupFunctionReg;
3356  Register vector = x9;
3357  Register scratch = x10;
3358  Label allocate_vector, done;
3359 
3360  __ LoadTaggedField(
3361  vector, FieldMemOperand(kWasmImplicitArgRegister,
3362  WasmTrustedInstanceData::kFeedbackVectorsOffset));
3363  __ Add(vector, vector, Operand(func_index, LSL, kTaggedSizeLog2));
3364  __ LoadTaggedField(vector,
3365  FieldMemOperand(vector, OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(FixedArray)));
3366  __ JumpIfSmi(vector, &allocate_vector);
3367  __ bind(&done);
3368  __ Push(vector, xzr);
3369  __ Ret();
3370 
3371  __ bind(&allocate_vector);
3372  // Feedback vector doesn't exist yet. Call the runtime to allocate it.
3373  // We temporarily change the frame type for this, because we need special
3374  // handling by the stack walker in case of GC.
3375  __ Mov(scratch, StackFrame::TypeToMarker(StackFrame::WASM_LIFTOFF_SETUP));
3376  __ Str(scratch, MemOperand(fp, TypedFrameConstants::kFrameTypeOffset));
3377  // Save registers.
3378  __ PushXRegList(kSavedGpRegs);
3379  __ PushQRegList(kSavedFpRegs);
3380  __ Push<MacroAssembler::kSignLR>(lr, xzr); // xzr is for alignment.
3381 
3382  // Arguments to the runtime function: instance data, func_index, and an
3383  // additional stack slot for the NativeModule. The first pushed register
3384  // is for alignment. {x0} and {x1} are picked arbitrarily.
3385  __ SmiTag(func_index);
3386  __ Push(x0, kWasmImplicitArgRegister, func_index, x1);
3387  __ Mov(cp, Smi::zero());
3388  __ CallRuntime(Runtime::kWasmAllocateFeedbackVector, 3);
3389  __ Mov(vector, kReturnRegister0);
3390 
3391  // Restore registers and frame type.
3392  __ Pop<MacroAssembler::kAuthLR>(xzr, lr);
3393  __ PopQRegList(kSavedFpRegs);
3394  __ PopXRegList(kSavedGpRegs);
3395  // Restore the instance data from the frame.
3396  __ Ldr(kWasmImplicitArgRegister,
3397  MemOperand(fp, WasmFrameConstants::kWasmInstanceDataOffset));
3398  __ Mov(scratch, StackFrame::TypeToMarker(StackFrame::WASM));
3399  __ Str(scratch, MemOperand(fp, TypedFrameConstants::kFrameTypeOffset));
3400  __ B(&done);
3401 }

3403 void Builtins::Generate_WasmCompileLazy(MacroAssembler* masm) {
3404  // The function index was put in w8 by the jump table trampoline.
3405  // Sign extend and convert to Smi for the runtime call.
3406  __ sxtw(kWasmCompileLazyFuncIndexRegister,
3407  kWasmCompileLazyFuncIndexRegister.W());
3408  __ SmiTag(kWasmCompileLazyFuncIndexRegister);
3409 
3410  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm);
3411  temps.Exclude(x17);
3412  {
3413  HardAbortScope hard_abort(masm); // Avoid calls to Abort.
3414  FrameScope scope(masm, StackFrame::INTERNAL);
3415  // Manually save the instance data (which kSavedGpRegs skips because its
3416  // other use puts it into the fixed frame anyway). The stack slot is valid
3417  // because the {FrameScope} (via {EnterFrame}) always reserves it (for stack
3418  // alignment reasons). The instance is needed because once this builtin is
3419  // done, we'll call a regular Wasm function.
3420  __ Str(kWasmImplicitArgRegister,
3421  MemOperand(fp, WasmFrameConstants::kWasmInstanceDataOffset));
3422 
3423  // Save registers that we need to keep alive across the runtime call.
3424  __ PushXRegList(kSavedGpRegs);
3425  __ PushQRegList(kSavedFpRegs);
3426 
3427  __ Push(kWasmImplicitArgRegister, kWasmCompileLazyFuncIndexRegister);
3428  // Initialize the JavaScript context with 0. CEntry will use it to
3429  // set the current context on the isolate.
3430  __ Mov(cp, Smi::zero());
3431  __ CallRuntime(Runtime::kWasmCompileLazy, 2);
3432 
3433  // Untag the returned Smi into into x17 (ip1), for later use.
3434  static_assert(!kSavedGpRegs.has(x17));
3435  __ SmiUntag(x17, kReturnRegister0);
3436 
3437  // Restore registers.
3438  __ PopQRegList(kSavedFpRegs);
3439  __ PopXRegList(kSavedGpRegs);
3440  // Restore the instance data from the frame.
3441  __ Ldr(kWasmImplicitArgRegister,
3442  MemOperand(fp, WasmFrameConstants::kWasmInstanceDataOffset));
3443  }
3444 
3445  // The runtime function returned the jump table slot offset as a Smi (now in
3446  // x17). Use that to compute the jump target. Use x17 (ip1) for the branch
3447  // target, to be compliant with CFI.
3448  constexpr Register temp = x8;
3449  static_assert(!kSavedGpRegs.has(temp));
3450  __ ldr(temp, FieldMemOperand(kWasmImplicitArgRegister,
3451  WasmTrustedInstanceData::kJumpTableStartOffset));
3452  __ add(x17, temp, Operand(x17));
3453  // Finally, jump to the jump table slot for the function.
3454  __ Jump(x17);
3455 }

3480 // Check that the stack was in the old state (if generated code assertions are
3481 // enabled), and switch to the new state.
3482 void SwitchStackState(MacroAssembler* masm, Register stack, Register tmp,
3483  wasm::JumpBuffer::StackState old_state,
3484  wasm::JumpBuffer::StackState new_state) {
3485 #if V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
3486  __ Ldr(tmp.W(), MemOperand(stack, wasm::kStackStateOffset));
3487  __ Cmp(tmp.W(), old_state);
3488  Label ok;
3489  __ B(&ok, eq);
3490  __ Trap();
3491  __ bind(&ok);
3492 #endif
3493  __ Mov(tmp.W(), new_state);
3494  __ Str(tmp.W(), MemOperand(stack, wasm::kStackStateOffset));
3495 }

3497 // Switch the stack pointer. Also switch the simulator's stack limit when
3498 // running on the simulator. This needs to be done as close as possible to
3499 // changing the stack pointer, as a mismatch between the stack pointer and the
3500 // simulator's stack limit can cause stack access check failures.
3501 void SwitchStackPointerAndSimulatorStackLimit(MacroAssembler* masm,
3502  Register stack, Register tmp) {
3503  if (masm->options().enable_simulator_code) {
3504  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm);
3505  temps.Exclude(x16);
3506  __ Ldr(tmp, MemOperand(stack, wasm::kStackSpOffset));
3507  __ Ldr(x16, MemOperand(stack, wasm::kStackLimitOffset));
3508  __ Mov(sp, tmp);
3509  __ hlt(kImmExceptionIsSwitchStackLimit);
3510  } else {
3511  __ Ldr(tmp, MemOperand(stack, wasm::kStackSpOffset));
3512  __ Mov(sp, tmp);
3513  }
3514 }

3516 void FillJumpBuffer(MacroAssembler* masm, Register stack, Label* pc,
3517  Register tmp) {

3522  __ Str(tmp, MemOperand(stack, wasm::kStackLimitOffset));
3523  __ Adr(tmp, pc);
3524  __ Str(tmp, MemOperand(stack, wasm::kStackPcOffset));

3527 void LoadJumpBuffer(MacroAssembler* masm, Register stack, bool load_pc,
3528  Register tmp, wasm::JumpBuffer::StackState expected_state) {

3532  if (load_pc) {
3533  __ Ldr(tmp, MemOperand(stack, wasm::kStackPcOffset));
3534  __ Br(tmp);
3535  }

3537  // lock.
3538 }

3549 // Updates the stack limit and central stack info, and validates the switch.
3550 void SwitchStacks(MacroAssembler* masm, Register old_stack, bool return_switch,
3551  const std::initializer_list<CPURegister> keep) {
3552  using ER = ExternalReference;
3553  for (size_t i = 0; i < (keep.size() & ~0x1); i += 2) {
3554  __ Push(keep.begin()[i], keep.begin()[i + 1]);
3555  }
3556  if (keep.size() % 2 == 1) {
3557  __ Push(*(keep.end() - 1), padreg);
3558  }
3559  {
3560  FrameScope scope(masm, StackFrame::MANUAL);
3561  // Move {old_stack} first in case it aliases kCArgRegs[0].
3562  __ Mov(kCArgRegs[1], old_stack);
3563  __ Mov(kCArgRegs[0], ExternalReference::isolate_address(masm->isolate()));
3564  __ CallCFunction(
3565  return_switch ? ER::wasm_return_switch() : ER::wasm_switch_stacks(), 2);
3566  }
3567  if (keep.size() % 2 == 1) {
3568  __ Pop(padreg, *(keep.end() - 1));
3569  }
3570  for (size_t i = (keep.size() & ~0x1); i > 0; i -= 2) {
3571  __ Pop(keep.begin()[i - 1], keep.begin()[i - 2]);
3572  }
3573 }

3575 void ReloadParentStack(MacroAssembler* masm, Register return_reg,
3576  Register return_value, Register context, Register tmp1,
3577  Register tmp2, Register tmp3) {
3578  Register active_stack = tmp1;
3579  __ LoadRootRelative(active_stack, IsolateData::active_stack_offset());
3580 
3581  // Set a null pointer in the jump buffer's SP slot to indicate to the stack
3582  // frame iterator that this stack is empty.
3583  __ Str(xzr, MemOperand(active_stack, wasm::kStackSpOffset));
3584  {
3585  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm);
3586  Register scratch = temps.AcquireX();
3587  SwitchStackState(masm, active_stack, scratch, wasm::JumpBuffer::Active,
3588  wasm::JumpBuffer::Retired);
3589  }
3590  Register parent = tmp2;
3591  __ Ldr(parent, MemOperand(active_stack, wasm::kStackParentOffset));
3592 
3593  // Update active stack.
3594  __ StoreRootRelative(IsolateData::active_stack_offset(), parent);
3595 
3596  // Switch stack!
3597  SwitchStacks(masm, active_stack, true,
3598  {return_reg, return_value, context, parent});
3599  LoadJumpBuffer(masm, parent, false, tmp3, wasm::JumpBuffer::Inactive);
3600 }

3619 // TODO(irezvov): Consolidate with arm RegisterAllocator.
3620 class RegisterAllocator {
3621  public:
3622  class Scoped {
3623  public:
3624  Scoped(RegisterAllocator* allocator, Register* reg):
3625  allocator_(allocator), reg_(reg) {}
3626  ~Scoped() { allocator_->Free(reg_); }
3627  private:
3628  RegisterAllocator* allocator_;
3629  Register* reg_;
3630  };
3631 
3632  explicit RegisterAllocator(const CPURegList& registers)
3633  : initial_(registers),
3634  available_(registers) {}
3635  void Ask(Register* reg) {
3636  DCHECK_EQ(*reg, no_reg);
3637  DCHECK(!available_.IsEmpty());
3638  *reg = available_.PopLowestIndex().X();
3639  allocated_registers_.push_back(reg);
3640  }
3641 
3642  void Pinned(const Register& requested, Register* reg) {
3643  DCHECK(available_.IncludesAliasOf(requested));
3644  *reg = requested;
3645  Reserve(requested);
3646  allocated_registers_.push_back(reg);
3647  }
3648 
3649  void Free(Register* reg) {
3650  DCHECK_NE(*reg, no_reg);
3651  available_.Combine(*reg);
3652  *reg = no_reg;
3653  allocated_registers_.erase(
3654  find(allocated_registers_.begin(), allocated_registers_.end(), reg));
3655  }
3656 
3657  void Reserve(const Register& reg) {
3658  if (reg == NoReg) {
3659  return;
3660  }
3661  DCHECK(available_.IncludesAliasOf(reg));
3662  available_.Remove(reg);
3663  }
3664 
3665  void Reserve(const Register& reg1,
3666  const Register& reg2,
3667  const Register& reg3 = NoReg,
3668  const Register& reg4 = NoReg,
3669  const Register& reg5 = NoReg,
3670  const Register& reg6 = NoReg) {
3671  Reserve(reg1);
3672  Reserve(reg2);
3673  Reserve(reg3);
3674  Reserve(reg4);
3675  Reserve(reg5);
3676  Reserve(reg6);
3677  }
3678 
3679  bool IsUsed(const Register& reg) {
3680  return initial_.IncludesAliasOf(reg)
3681  && !available_.IncludesAliasOf(reg);
3682  }
3683 
3684  void ResetExcept(const Register& reg1 = NoReg,
3685  const Register& reg2 = NoReg,
3686  const Register& reg3 = NoReg,
3687  const Register& reg4 = NoReg,
3688  const Register& reg5 = NoReg,
3689  const Register& reg6 = NoReg) {
3690  available_ = initial_;
3691  if (reg1 != NoReg) {
3692  available_.Remove(reg1, reg2, reg3, reg4);
3693  }
3694  if (reg5 != NoReg) {
3695  available_.Remove(reg5, reg6);
3696  }
3697  auto it = allocated_registers_.begin();
3698  while (it != allocated_registers_.end()) {
3699  if (available_.IncludesAliasOf(**it)) {
3700  **it = no_reg;
3701  it = allocated_registers_.erase(it);
3702  } else {
3703  it++;
3704  }
3705  }
3706  }
3707 
3708  static RegisterAllocator WithAllocatableGeneralRegisters() {
3709  CPURegList list(kXRegSizeInBits, RegList());
3710  const RegisterConfiguration* config(RegisterConfiguration::Default());
3711  list.set_bits(config->allocatable_general_codes_mask());
3712  return RegisterAllocator(list);
3713  }
3714 
3715  private:
3716  std::vector<Register*> allocated_registers_;
3717  const CPURegList initial_;
3718  CPURegList available_;
3719 };

3748 // Loads the context field of the WasmTrustedInstanceData or WasmImportData
3749 // depending on the data's type, and places the result in the input register.
3750 void GetContextFromImplicitArg(MacroAssembler* masm, Register data,
3751  Register scratch) {
3752  __ LoadTaggedField(scratch, FieldMemOperand(data, HeapObject::kMapOffset));
3753  __ CompareInstanceType(scratch, scratch, WASM_TRUSTED_INSTANCE_DATA_TYPE);
3754  Label instance;
3755  Label end;
3756  __ B(eq, &instance);
3757  __ LoadTaggedField(
3758  data, FieldMemOperand(data, WasmImportData::kNativeContextOffset));
3759  __ jmp(&end);
3760  __ bind(&instance);
3761  __ LoadTaggedField(
3762  data,
3763  FieldMemOperand(data, WasmTrustedInstanceData::kNativeContextOffset));
3764  __ bind(&end);
3765 }

3791 void Builtins::Generate_WasmSuspend(MacroAssembler* masm) {
3792  auto regs = RegisterAllocator::WithAllocatableGeneralRegisters();
3793  // Set up the stackframe.
3794  __ EnterFrame(StackFrame::STACK_SWITCH);
3795 
3796  DEFINE_PINNED(suspender, x0);
3797  DEFINE_PINNED(context, kContextRegister);
3798 
3799  __ Sub(sp, sp,
3800  Immediate(StackSwitchFrameConstants::kNumSpillSlots *
3801  kSystemPointerSize));
3802  // Set a sentinel value for the spill slots visited by the GC.
3803  ResetStackSwitchFrameStackSlots(masm);
3804 
3805  // -------------------------------------------
3806  // Save current state in active jump buffer.
3807  // -------------------------------------------
3808  Label resume;
3809  DEFINE_REG(stack);
3810  __ LoadRootRelative(stack, IsolateData::active_stack_offset());
3811  DEFINE_REG(scratch);
3812  FillJumpBuffer(masm, stack, &resume, scratch);
3813  SwitchStackState(masm, stack, scratch, wasm::JumpBuffer::Active,
3814  wasm::JumpBuffer::Suspended);
3815  regs.ResetExcept(suspender, stack);
3816 
3817  DEFINE_REG(suspender_stack);
3818  __ LoadExternalPointerField(
3819  suspender_stack,
3820  FieldMemOperand(suspender, WasmSuspenderObject::kStackOffset),
3821  kWasmStackMemoryTag);
3822  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
3823  // -------------------------------------------
3824  // Check that the suspender's stack is the active stack.
3825  // -------------------------------------------
3826  // TODO(thibaudm): Once we add core stack-switching instructions, this
3827  // check will not hold anymore: it's possible that the active stack changed
3828  // (due to an internal switch), so we have to update the suspender.
3829  __ cmp(suspender_stack, stack);
3830  Label ok;
3831  __ B(&ok, eq);
3832  __ Trap();
3833  __ bind(&ok);
3834  }
3835  // -------------------------------------------
3836  // Update roots.
3837  // -------------------------------------------
3838  DEFINE_REG(caller);
3839  __ Ldr(caller, MemOperand(suspender_stack, wasm::kStackParentOffset));
3840  __ StoreRootRelative(IsolateData::active_stack_offset(), caller);
3841  DEFINE_REG(parent);
3842  __ LoadTaggedField(
3843  parent, FieldMemOperand(suspender, WasmSuspenderObject::kParentOffset));
3844  int32_t active_suspender_offset =
3845  MacroAssembler::RootRegisterOffsetForRootIndex(
3846  RootIndex::kActiveSuspender);
3847  __ Str(parent, MemOperand(kRootRegister, active_suspender_offset));
3848  regs.ResetExcept(suspender, caller, stack);
3849 
3850  // -------------------------------------------
3851  // Load jump buffer.
3852  // -------------------------------------------
3853  SwitchStacks(masm, stack, false, {caller, suspender});
3854  FREE_REG(stack);
3855  __ LoadTaggedField(
3856  kReturnRegister0,
3857  FieldMemOperand(suspender, WasmSuspenderObject::kPromiseOffset));
3858  MemOperand GCScanSlotPlace =
3859  MemOperand(fp, StackSwitchFrameConstants::kGCScanSlotCountOffset);
3860  __ Str(xzr, GCScanSlotPlace);
3861  ASSIGN_REG(scratch)
3862  LoadJumpBuffer(masm, caller, true, scratch, wasm::JumpBuffer::Inactive);
3863  __ Trap();
3864  __ Bind(&resume, BranchTargetIdentifier::kBtiJump);
3865  __ LeaveFrame(StackFrame::STACK_SWITCH);
3866  __ Ret(lr);
3867 }

3869 namespace {
3870 // Resume the suspender stored in the closure. We generate two variants of this
3871 // builtin: the onFulfilled variant resumes execution at the saved PC and
3872 // forwards the value, the onRejected variant throws the value.
3873 
3874 void Generate_WasmResumeHelper(MacroAssembler* masm, wasm::OnResume on_resume) {
3875  auto regs = RegisterAllocator::WithAllocatableGeneralRegisters();
3876  __ EnterFrame(StackFrame::STACK_SWITCH);
3877 
3878  DEFINE_PINNED(closure, kJSFunctionRegister); // x1
3879 
3880  __ Sub(sp, sp,
3881  Immediate(StackSwitchFrameConstants::kNumSpillSlots *
3882  kSystemPointerSize));
3883  // Set a sentinel value for the spill slots visited by the GC.
3884  ResetStackSwitchFrameStackSlots(masm);
3885 
3886  regs.ResetExcept(closure);
3887 
3888  // -------------------------------------------
3889  // Load suspender from closure.
3890  // -------------------------------------------
3891  DEFINE_REG(sfi);
3892  __ LoadTaggedField(
3893  sfi,
3894  MemOperand(
3895  closure,
3896  wasm::ObjectAccess::SharedFunctionInfoOffsetInTaggedJSFunction()));
3897  FREE_REG(closure);
3898  // Suspender should be ObjectRegister register to be used in
3899  // RecordWriteField calls later.
3900  DEFINE_PINNED(suspender, WriteBarrierDescriptor::ObjectRegister());
3901  DEFINE_REG(resume_data);
3902  __ LoadTaggedField(
3903  resume_data,
3904  FieldMemOperand(sfi, SharedFunctionInfo::kUntrustedFunctionDataOffset));
3905  // The write barrier uses a fixed register for the host object (rdi). The next
3906  // barrier is on the suspender, so load it in rdi directly.
3907  __ LoadTaggedField(
3908  suspender,
3909  FieldMemOperand(resume_data, WasmResumeData::kSuspenderOffset));
3910  regs.ResetExcept(suspender);
3911 
3912  // -------------------------------------------
3913  // Save current state.
3914  // -------------------------------------------
3915  Label suspend;
3916  DEFINE_REG(active_stack);
3917  __ LoadRootRelative(active_stack, IsolateData::active_stack_offset());
3918  DEFINE_REG(scratch);
3919  FillJumpBuffer(masm, active_stack, &suspend, scratch);
3920  SwitchStackState(masm, active_stack, scratch, wasm::JumpBuffer::Active,
3921  wasm::JumpBuffer::Inactive);
3922 
3923  // -------------------------------------------
3924  // Set the suspender and stack parents and update the roots
3925  // -------------------------------------------
3926  DEFINE_REG(active_suspender);
3927  __ LoadRoot(active_suspender, RootIndex::kActiveSuspender);
3928  __ StoreTaggedField(
3929  active_suspender,
3930  FieldMemOperand(suspender, WasmSuspenderObject::kParentOffset));
3931  __ RecordWriteField(suspender, WasmSuspenderObject::kParentOffset,
3932  active_suspender, kLRHasBeenSaved,
3933  SaveFPRegsMode::kIgnore);
3934  int32_t active_suspender_offset =
3935  MacroAssembler::RootRegisterOffsetForRootIndex(
3936  RootIndex::kActiveSuspender);
3937  __ Str(suspender, MemOperand(kRootRegister, active_suspender_offset));
3938 
3939  DEFINE_REG(target_stack);
3940  __ LoadExternalPointerField(
3941  target_stack,
3942  FieldMemOperand(suspender, WasmSuspenderObject::kStackOffset),
3943  kWasmStackMemoryTag);
3944  FREE_REG(suspender);
3945 
3946  __ StoreRootRelative(IsolateData::active_stack_offset(), target_stack);
3947 
3948  SwitchStacks(masm, active_stack, false, {target_stack});
3949 
3950  regs.ResetExcept(target_stack);
3951 
3952  // -------------------------------------------
3953  // Load state from target jmpbuf (longjmp).
3954  // -------------------------------------------
3955  regs.Reserve(kReturnRegister0);
3956  ASSIGN_REG(scratch);
3957  // Move resolved value to return register.
3958  __ Ldr(kReturnRegister0, MemOperand(fp, 3 * kSystemPointerSize));
3959  MemOperand GCScanSlotPlace =
3960  MemOperand(fp, StackSwitchFrameConstants::kGCScanSlotCountOffset);
3961  __ Str(xzr, GCScanSlotPlace);
3962  if (on_resume == wasm::OnResume::kThrow) {
3963  // Switch without restoring the PC.
3964  LoadJumpBuffer(masm, target_stack, false, scratch,
3965  wasm::JumpBuffer::Suspended);
3966  // Pop this frame now. The unwinder expects that the first STACK_SWITCH
3967  // frame is the outermost one.
3968  __ LeaveFrame(StackFrame::STACK_SWITCH);
3969  // Forward the onRejected value to kThrow.
3970  __ Push(xzr, kReturnRegister0);
3971  __ CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrow);
3972  } else {
3973  // Resume the stack normally.
3974  LoadJumpBuffer(masm, target_stack, true, scratch,
3975  wasm::JumpBuffer::Suspended);
3976  }
3977  __ Trap();
3978  __ Bind(&suspend, BranchTargetIdentifier::kBtiJump);
3979  __ LeaveFrame(StackFrame::STACK_SWITCH);
3980  // Pop receiver + parameter.
3981  __ DropArguments(2);
3982  __ Ret(lr);
3983 }

4004  DEFINE_SCOPED(scratch)
4005  DEFINE_REG(parent_stack)
4006  __ LoadRootRelative(parent_stack, IsolateData::active_stack_offset());
4007  __ Ldr(parent_stack, MemOperand(parent_stack, wasm::kStackParentOffset));
4008  FillJumpBuffer(masm, parent_stack, suspend, scratch);
4009  SwitchStacks(masm, parent_stack, false, {wasm_instance, wrapper_buffer});
4010  FREE_REG(parent_stack);
4011  // Save the old stack's fp in x9, and use it to access the parameters in
4012  // the parent frame.
4013  regs.Pinned(x9, &original_fp);
4014  __ Mov(original_fp, fp);
4015  DEFINE_REG(target_stack);
4016  __ LoadRootRelative(target_stack, IsolateData::active_stack_offset());
4017  LoadTargetJumpBuffer(masm, target_stack, scratch,
4018  wasm::JumpBuffer::Suspended);
4019  FREE_REG(target_stack);
4020  // Push the loaded fp. We know it is null, because there is no frame yet,
4021  // so we could also push 0 directly. In any case we need to push it,
4022  // because this marks the base of the stack segment for
4023  // the stack frame iterator.
4024  __ EnterFrame(StackFrame::STACK_SWITCH);
4025  int stack_space =
4026  RoundUp(StackSwitchFrameConstants::kNumSpillSlots * kSystemPointerSize +
4027  JSToWasmWrapperFrameConstants::kWrapperBufferSize,
4028  16);
4029  __ Sub(sp, sp, Immediate(stack_space));
4030  ASSIGN_REG(new_wrapper_buffer)
4031  __ Mov(new_wrapper_buffer, sp);
4032  // Copy data needed for return handling from old wrapper buffer to new one.
4033  // kWrapperBufferRefReturnCount will be copied too, because 8 bytes are copied
4034  // at the same time.
4035  static_assert(JSToWasmWrapperFrameConstants::kWrapperBufferRefReturnCount ==
4036  JSToWasmWrapperFrameConstants::kWrapperBufferReturnCount + 4);
4037  __ Ldr(scratch,
4038  MemOperand(wrapper_buffer,
4039  JSToWasmWrapperFrameConstants::kWrapperBufferReturnCount));
4040  __ Str(scratch,
4041  MemOperand(new_wrapper_buffer,
4042  JSToWasmWrapperFrameConstants::kWrapperBufferReturnCount));
4043  __ Ldr(
4044  scratch,
4045  MemOperand(
4046  wrapper_buffer,
4047  JSToWasmWrapperFrameConstants::kWrapperBufferSigRepresentationArray));
4048  __ Str(
4049  scratch,
4050  MemOperand(
4051  new_wrapper_buffer,
4052  JSToWasmWrapperFrameConstants::kWrapperBufferSigRepresentationArray));
4053 }

4055 void SwitchBackAndReturnPromise(MacroAssembler* masm, RegisterAllocator& regs,
4056  wasm::Promise mode, Label* return_promise) {
4057  regs.ResetExcept();
4058  // The return value of the wasm function becomes the parameter of the
4059  // FulfillPromise builtin, and the promise is the return value of this
4060  // wrapper.
4061  static const Builtin_FulfillPromise_InterfaceDescriptor desc;
4062  DEFINE_PINNED(promise, desc.GetRegisterParameter(0));
4063  DEFINE_PINNED(return_value, desc.GetRegisterParameter(1));
4064  DEFINE_SCOPED(tmp);
4065  DEFINE_SCOPED(tmp2);
4066  DEFINE_SCOPED(tmp3);
4067  if (mode == wasm::kPromise) {
4068  __ Move(return_value, kReturnRegister0);
4069  __ LoadRoot(promise, RootIndex::kActiveSuspender);
4070  __ LoadTaggedField(
4071  promise, FieldMemOperand(promise, WasmSuspenderObject::kPromiseOffset));
4072  }
4073  __ Ldr(kContextRegister,
4074  MemOperand(fp, StackSwitchFrameConstants::kImplicitArgOffset));
4075  GetContextFromImplicitArg(masm, kContextRegister, tmp);
4076 
4077  ReloadParentStack(masm, promise, return_value, kContextRegister, tmp, tmp2,
4078  tmp3);
4079  RestoreParentSuspender(masm, tmp);
4080 
4081  if (mode == wasm::kPromise) {
4082  __ Mov(tmp, 1);
4083  __ Str(tmp,
4084  MemOperand(fp, StackSwitchFrameConstants::kGCScanSlotCountOffset));
4085  __ Push(padreg, promise);
4086  __ CallBuiltin(Builtin::kFulfillPromise);
4087  __ Pop(promise, padreg);
4088  }
4089  FREE_REG(promise);
4090  FREE_REG(return_value);
4091  __ bind(return_promise);
4092 }

4094 void GenerateExceptionHandlingLandingPad(MacroAssembler* masm,
4095  RegisterAllocator& regs,
4096  Label* return_promise) {
4097  regs.ResetExcept();
4098  static const Builtin_RejectPromise_InterfaceDescriptor desc;
4099  DEFINE_PINNED(promise, desc.GetRegisterParameter(0));
4100  DEFINE_PINNED(reason, desc.GetRegisterParameter(1));
4101  DEFINE_PINNED(debug_event, desc.GetRegisterParameter(2));
4102  int catch_handler = __ pc_offset();
4103  __ JumpTarget();
4104 
4105  DEFINE_SCOPED(thread_in_wasm_flag_addr);
4106  thread_in_wasm_flag_addr = x2;
4107  // Unset thread_in_wasm_flag.
4108  __ Ldr(
4109  thread_in_wasm_flag_addr,
4110  MemOperand(kRootRegister, Isolate::thread_in_wasm_flag_address_offset()));
4111  __ Str(wzr, MemOperand(thread_in_wasm_flag_addr, 0));
4112 
4113  // The exception becomes the parameter of the RejectPromise builtin, and the
4114  // promise is the return value of this wrapper.
4115  __ Move(reason, kReturnRegister0);
4116  __ LoadRoot(promise, RootIndex::kActiveSuspender);
4117  __ LoadTaggedField(
4118  promise, FieldMemOperand(promise, WasmSuspenderObject::kPromiseOffset));
4119 
4120  __ Ldr(kContextRegister,
4121  MemOperand(fp, StackSwitchFrameConstants::kImplicitArgOffset));
4122 
4123  DEFINE_SCOPED(tmp);
4124  DEFINE_SCOPED(tmp2);
4125  DEFINE_SCOPED(tmp3);
4126  GetContextFromImplicitArg(masm, kContextRegister, tmp);
4127  ReloadParentStack(masm, promise, reason, kContextRegister, tmp, tmp2, tmp3);
4128  RestoreParentSuspender(masm, tmp);
4129 
4130  __ Mov(tmp, 1);
4131  __ Str(tmp,
4132  MemOperand(fp, StackSwitchFrameConstants::kGCScanSlotCountOffset));
4133  __ Push(padreg, promise);
4134  __ LoadRoot(debug_event, RootIndex::kTrueValue);
4135  __ CallBuiltin(Builtin::kRejectPromise);
4136  __ Pop(promise, padreg);
4137 
4138  // Run the rest of the wrapper normally (deconstruct the frame, ...).
4139  __ jmp(return_promise);
4140 
4141  masm->isolate()->builtins()->SetJSPIPromptHandlerOffset(catch_handler);
4142 }

4144 void JSToWasmWrapperHelper(MacroAssembler* masm, wasm::Promise mode) {
4145  bool stack_switch = mode == wasm::kPromise || mode == wasm::kStressSwitch;
4146  auto regs = RegisterAllocator::WithAllocatableGeneralRegisters();
4147 
4148  __ EnterFrame(stack_switch ? StackFrame::STACK_SWITCH
4149  : StackFrame::JS_TO_WASM);
4150 
4151  __ Sub(sp, sp,
4152  Immediate(StackSwitchFrameConstants::kNumSpillSlots *
4153  kSystemPointerSize));
4154 
4155  // Load the implicit argument (instance data or import data) from the frame.
4156  DEFINE_PINNED(implicit_arg, kWasmImplicitArgRegister);
4157  __ Ldr(implicit_arg,
4158  MemOperand(fp, JSToWasmWrapperFrameConstants::kImplicitArgOffset));
4159 
4160  DEFINE_PINNED(wrapper_buffer,
4161  WasmJSToWasmWrapperDescriptor::WrapperBufferRegister());
4162 
4163  Label suspend;
4164  Register original_fp = no_reg;
4165  Register new_wrapper_buffer = no_reg;
4166  if (stack_switch) {
4167  SwitchToAllocatedStack(masm, regs, implicit_arg, wrapper_buffer,
4168  original_fp, new_wrapper_buffer, &suspend);
4169  } else {
4170  original_fp = fp;
4171  new_wrapper_buffer = wrapper_buffer;
4172  }
4173 
4174  regs.ResetExcept(original_fp, wrapper_buffer, implicit_arg,
4175  new_wrapper_buffer);
4176 
4177  {
4178  __ Str(new_wrapper_buffer,
4179  MemOperand(fp, JSToWasmWrapperFrameConstants::kWrapperBufferOffset));
4180  if (stack_switch) {
4181  __ Str(implicit_arg,
4182  MemOperand(fp, StackSwitchFrameConstants::kImplicitArgOffset));
4183  DEFINE_SCOPED(scratch)
4184  __ Ldr(
4185  scratch,
4186  MemOperand(original_fp,
4187  JSToWasmWrapperFrameConstants::kResultArrayParamOffset));
4188  __ Str(scratch,
4189  MemOperand(fp, StackSwitchFrameConstants::kResultArrayOffset));
4190  }
4191  }
4192  {
4193  DEFINE_SCOPED(result_size);
4194  __ Ldr(result_size,
4195  MemOperand(wrapper_buffer, JSToWasmWrapperFrameConstants::
4196  kWrapperBufferStackReturnBufferSize));
4197  // The `result_size` is the number of slots needed on the stack to store the
4198  // return values of the wasm function. If `result_size` is an odd number, we
4199  // have to add `1` to preserve stack pointer alignment.
4200  __ Add(result_size, result_size, 1);
4201  __ Bic(result_size, result_size, 1);
4202  __ Sub(sp, sp, Operand(result_size, LSL, kSystemPointerSizeLog2));
4203  }
4204  {
4205  DEFINE_SCOPED(scratch);
4206  __ Mov(scratch, sp);
4207  __ Str(scratch, MemOperand(new_wrapper_buffer,
4208  JSToWasmWrapperFrameConstants::
4209  kWrapperBufferStackReturnBufferStart));
4210  }
4211  if (stack_switch) {
4212  FREE_REG(new_wrapper_buffer)
4213  }
4214  FREE_REG(implicit_arg)
4215  for (auto reg : wasm::kGpParamRegisters) {
4216  regs.Reserve(reg);
4217  }
4218 
4219  // The first GP parameter holds the trusted instance data or the import data.
4220  // This is handled specially.
4221  int stack_params_offset =
4222  (arraysize(wasm::kGpParamRegisters) - 1) * kSystemPointerSize +
4223  arraysize(wasm::kFpParamRegisters) * kDoubleSize;
4224 
4225  {
4226  DEFINE_SCOPED(params_start);
4227  __ Ldr(params_start,
4228  MemOperand(wrapper_buffer,
4229  JSToWasmWrapperFrameConstants::kWrapperBufferParamStart));
4230  {
4231  // Push stack parameters on the stack.
4232  DEFINE_SCOPED(params_end);
4233  __ Ldr(params_end,
4234  MemOperand(wrapper_buffer,
4235  JSToWasmWrapperFrameConstants::kWrapperBufferParamEnd));
4236  DEFINE_SCOPED(last_stack_param);
4237 
4238  __ Add(last_stack_param, params_start, Immediate(stack_params_offset));
4239  Label loop_start;
4240  {
4241  DEFINE_SCOPED(scratch);
4242  // Check if there is an even number of parameters, so no alignment
4243  // needed.
4244  __ Sub(scratch, params_end, last_stack_param);
4245  __ TestAndBranchIfAllClear(scratch, 0x8, &loop_start);
4246 
4247  // Push the first parameter with alignment.
4248  __ Ldr(scratch, MemOperand(params_end, -kSystemPointerSize, PreIndex));
4249  __ Push(xzr, scratch);
4250  }
4251  __ bind(&loop_start);
4252 
4253  Label finish_stack_params;
4254  __ Cmp(last_stack_param, params_end);
4255  __ B(ge, &finish_stack_params);
4256 
4257  // Push parameter
4258  {
4259  DEFINE_SCOPED(scratch1);
4260  DEFINE_SCOPED(scratch2);
4261  __ Ldp(scratch2, scratch1,
4262  MemOperand(params_end, -2 * kSystemPointerSize, PreIndex));
4263  __ Push(scratch1, scratch2);
4264  }
4265  __ jmp(&loop_start);
4266 
4267  __ bind(&finish_stack_params);
4268  }
4269 
4270  size_t next_offset = 0;
4271  for (size_t i = 1; i < arraysize(wasm::kGpParamRegisters); i += 2) {
4272  // Check that {params_start} does not overlap with any of the parameter
4273  // registers, so that we don't overwrite it by accident with the loads
4274  // below.
4275  DCHECK_NE(params_start, wasm::kGpParamRegisters[i]);
4276  DCHECK_NE(params_start, wasm::kGpParamRegisters[i + 1]);
4277  __ Ldp(wasm::kGpParamRegisters[i], wasm::kGpParamRegisters[i + 1],
4278  MemOperand(params_start, next_offset));
4279  next_offset += 2 * kSystemPointerSize;
4280  }
4281 
4282  for (size_t i = 0; i < arraysize(wasm::kFpParamRegisters); i += 2) {
4283  __ Ldp(wasm::kFpParamRegisters[i], wasm::kFpParamRegisters[i + 1],
4284  MemOperand(params_start, next_offset));
4285  next_offset += 2 * kDoubleSize;
4286  }
4287  DCHECK_EQ(next_offset, stack_params_offset);
4288  }
4289 
4290  {
4291  DEFINE_SCOPED(thread_in_wasm_flag_addr);
4292  __ Ldr(thread_in_wasm_flag_addr,
4293  MemOperand(kRootRegister,
4294  Isolate::thread_in_wasm_flag_address_offset()));
4295  DEFINE_SCOPED(scratch);
4296  __ Mov(scratch, 1);
4297  __ Str(scratch.W(), MemOperand(thread_in_wasm_flag_addr, 0));
4298  }
4299  __ Str(xzr,
4300  MemOperand(fp, StackSwitchFrameConstants::kGCScanSlotCountOffset));
4301  {
4302  DEFINE_SCOPED(call_target);
4303  __ LoadWasmCodePointer(
4304  call_target,
4305  MemOperand(wrapper_buffer,
4306  JSToWasmWrapperFrameConstants::kWrapperBufferCallTarget));
4307  // We do the call without a signature check here, since the wrapper loaded
4308  // the signature from the same trusted object as the call target to set up
4309  // the stack layout. We could add a signature hash and pass it through to
4310  // verify it here, but an attacker that could corrupt the signature could
4311  // also corrupt that signature hash (which is outside of the sandbox).
4312  __ CallWasmCodePointerNoSignatureCheck(call_target);
4313  }
4314  regs.ResetExcept();
4315  // The wrapper_buffer has to be in x2 as the correct parameter register.
4316  regs.Reserve(kReturnRegister0, kReturnRegister1);
4317  ASSIGN_PINNED(wrapper_buffer, x2);
4318  {
4319  DEFINE_SCOPED(thread_in_wasm_flag_addr);
4320  __ Ldr(thread_in_wasm_flag_addr,
4321  MemOperand(kRootRegister,
4322  Isolate::thread_in_wasm_flag_address_offset()));
4323  __ Str(wzr, MemOperand(thread_in_wasm_flag_addr, 0));
4324  }
4325 
4326  __ Ldr(wrapper_buffer,
4327  MemOperand(fp, JSToWasmWrapperFrameConstants::kWrapperBufferOffset));
4328 
4329  __ Str(wasm::kFpReturnRegisters[0],
4330  MemOperand(
4331  wrapper_buffer,
4332  JSToWasmWrapperFrameConstants::kWrapperBufferFPReturnRegister1));
4333  __ Str(wasm::kFpReturnRegisters[1],
4334  MemOperand(
4335  wrapper_buffer,
4336  JSToWasmWrapperFrameConstants::kWrapperBufferFPReturnRegister2));
4337  __ Str(wasm::kGpReturnRegisters[0],
4338  MemOperand(
4339  wrapper_buffer,
4340  JSToWasmWrapperFrameConstants::kWrapperBufferGPReturnRegister1));
4341  __ Str(wasm::kGpReturnRegisters[1],
4342  MemOperand(
4343  wrapper_buffer,
4344  JSToWasmWrapperFrameConstants::kWrapperBufferGPReturnRegister2));
4345  // Call the return value builtin with
4346  // x0: wasm instance.
4347  // x1: the result JSArray for multi-return.
4348  // x2: pointer to the byte buffer which contains all parameters.
4349  if (stack_switch) {
4350  __ Ldr(x1, MemOperand(fp, StackSwitchFrameConstants::kResultArrayOffset));
4351  __ Ldr(x0, MemOperand(fp, StackSwitchFrameConstants::kImplicitArgOffset));
4352  } else {
4353  __ Ldr(x1, MemOperand(
4354  fp, JSToWasmWrapperFrameConstants::kResultArrayParamOffset));
4355  __ Ldr(x0,
4356  MemOperand(fp, JSToWasmWrapperFrameConstants::kImplicitArgOffset));
4357  }
4358  Register scratch = x3;
4359  GetContextFromImplicitArg(masm, x0, scratch);
4360  __ CallBuiltin(Builtin::kJSToWasmHandleReturns);
4361 
4362  Label return_promise;
4363  if (stack_switch) {
4364  SwitchBackAndReturnPromise(masm, regs, mode, &return_promise);
4365  }
4366  __ Bind(&suspend, BranchTargetIdentifier::kBtiJump);
4367 
4368  __ LeaveFrame(stack_switch ? StackFrame::STACK_SWITCH
4369  : StackFrame::JS_TO_WASM);
4370  // Despite returning to the different location for regular and stack switching
4371  // versions, incoming argument count matches both cases:
4372  // instance and result array without suspend or
4373  // or promise resolve/reject params for callback.
4374  constexpr int64_t stack_arguments_in = 2;
4375  __ DropArguments(stack_arguments_in);
4376  __ Ret();
4377 
4378  // Catch handler for the stack-switching wrapper: reject the promise with the
4379  // thrown exception.
4380  if (mode == wasm::kPromise) {
4381  GenerateExceptionHandlingLandingPad(masm, regs, &return_promise);
4382  }
4383 }

4409 static constexpr Register kSwitchFlagRegister = x24;
4410 
4411 void SwitchToTheCentralStackIfNeeded(MacroAssembler* masm, Register argc_input,
4412  Register target_input,
4413  Register argv_input) {
4414  using ER = ExternalReference;
4415 
4416  __ Mov(kSwitchFlagRegister, 0);
4417  __ Mov(kOldSPRegister, sp);
4418 
4419  // Using x2-x4 as temporary registers, because they will be rewritten
4420  // before exiting to native code anyway.
4421 
4422  ER on_central_stack_flag_loc = ER::Create(
4423  IsolateAddressId::kIsOnCentralStackFlagAddress, masm->isolate());
4424  const Register& on_central_stack_flag = x2;
4425  __ Mov(on_central_stack_flag, on_central_stack_flag_loc);
4426  __ Ldrb(on_central_stack_flag, MemOperand(on_central_stack_flag));
4427 
4428  Label do_not_need_to_switch;
4429  __ Cbnz(on_central_stack_flag, &do_not_need_to_switch);
4430  // Switch to central stack.
4431 
4432  static constexpr Register central_stack_sp = x4;
4433  DCHECK(!AreAliased(central_stack_sp, argc_input, argv_input, target_input));
4434  {
4435  __ Push(argc_input, target_input, argv_input, padreg);
4436  __ Mov(kCArgRegs[0], ER::isolate_address());
4437  __ Mov(kCArgRegs[1], kOldSPRegister);
4438  __ CallCFunction(ER::wasm_switch_to_the_central_stack(), 2,
4439  SetIsolateDataSlots::kNo);
4440  __ Mov(central_stack_sp, kReturnRegister0);
4441  __ Pop(padreg, argv_input, target_input, argc_input);
4442  }
4443  {
4444  // Update the sp saved in the frame.
4445  // It will be used to calculate the callee pc during GC.
4446  // The pc is going to be on the new stack segment, so rewrite it here.
4447  UseScratchRegisterScope temps{masm};
4448  Register new_sp_after_call = temps.AcquireX();
4449  __ Sub(new_sp_after_call, central_stack_sp, kSystemPointerSize);
4450  __ Str(new_sp_after_call, MemOperand(fp, ExitFrameConstants::kSPOffset));
4451  }
4452 
4453  SwitchSimulatorStackLimit(masm);
4454 
4455  static constexpr int kReturnAddressSlotOffset = 1 * kSystemPointerSize;
4456  static constexpr int kPadding = 1 * kSystemPointerSize;
4457  __ Sub(sp, central_stack_sp, kReturnAddressSlotOffset + kPadding);
4458  __ Mov(kSwitchFlagRegister, 1);
4459 
4460  __ bind(&do_not_need_to_switch);
4461 }

4463 void SwitchFromTheCentralStackIfNeeded(MacroAssembler* masm) {
4464  using ER = ExternalReference;
4465 
4466  Label no_stack_change;
4467  __ Cbz(kSwitchFlagRegister, &no_stack_change);
4468 
4469  {
4470  __ Push(kReturnRegister0, kReturnRegister1);
4471  __ Mov(kCArgRegs[0], ER::isolate_address());
4472  __ CallCFunction(ER::wasm_switch_from_the_central_stack(), 1,
4473  SetIsolateDataSlots::kNo);
4474  __ Pop(kReturnRegister1, kReturnRegister0);
4475  }
4476 
4477  SwitchSimulatorStackLimit(masm);
4478 
4479  __ Mov(sp, kOldSPRegister);
4480 
4481  __ bind(&no_stack_change);
4482 }

4487 
4488 void Builtins::Generate_CEntry(MacroAssembler* masm, int result_size,
4489  ArgvMode argv_mode, bool builtin_exit_frame,
4490  bool switch_to_central_stack) {
4491  ASM_LOCATION("CEntry::Generate entry");
4492 
4493  using ER = ExternalReference;
4494 
4495  // Register parameters:
4496  // x0: argc (including receiver, untagged)
4497  // x1: target
4498  // If argv_mode == ArgvMode::kRegister:
4499  // x11: argv (pointer to first argument)
4500  //
4501  // The stack on entry holds the arguments and the receiver, with the receiver
4502  // at the highest address:
4503  //
4504  // sp[argc-1]: receiver
4505  // sp[argc-2]: arg[argc-2]
4506  // ... ...
4507  // sp[1]: arg[1]
4508  // sp[0]: arg[0]
4509  //
4510  // The arguments are in reverse order, so that arg[argc-2] is actually the
4511  // first argument to the target function and arg[0] is the last.
4512  static constexpr Register argc_input = x0;
4513  static constexpr Register target_input = x1;
4514  // Initialized below if ArgvMode::kStack.
4515  static constexpr Register argv_input = x11;
4516 
4517  if (argv_mode == ArgvMode::kStack) {
4518  // Derive argv from the stack pointer so that it points to the first
4519  // argument.
4520  __ SlotAddress(argv_input, argc_input);
4521  __ Sub(argv_input, argv_input, kReceiverOnStackSize);
4522  }
4523 
4524  // If ArgvMode::kStack, argc is reused below and must be retained across the
4525  // call in a callee-saved register.
4526  static constexpr Register argc = x22;
4527 
4528  // Enter the exit frame.
4529  const int kNoExtraSpace = 0;
4530  FrameScope scope(masm, StackFrame::MANUAL);
4531  __ EnterExitFrame(
4532  x10, kNoExtraSpace,
4533  builtin_exit_frame ? StackFrame::BUILTIN_EXIT : StackFrame::EXIT);
4534 
4535  if (argv_mode == ArgvMode::kStack) {
4536  __ Mov(argc, argc_input);
4537  }
4538 
4539 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4540  if (switch_to_central_stack) {
4541  SwitchToTheCentralStackIfNeeded(masm, argc_input, target_input, argv_input);
4542  }
4543 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4544 
4545  // x21 : argv
4546  // x22 : argc
4547  // x23 : call target
4548  //
4549  // The stack (on entry) holds the arguments and the receiver, with the
4550  // receiver at the highest address:
4551  //
4552  // argv[8]: receiver
4553  // argv -> argv[0]: arg[argc-2]
4554  // ... ...
4555  // argv[...]: arg[1]
4556  // argv[...]: arg[0]
4557  //
4558  // Immediately below (after) this is the exit frame, as constructed by
4559  // EnterExitFrame:
4560  // fp[8]: CallerPC (lr)
4561  // fp -> fp[0]: CallerFP (old fp)
4562  // fp[-8]: Space reserved for SPOffset.
4563  // fp[-16]: CodeObject()
4564  // sp[...]: Saved doubles, if saved_doubles is true.
4565  // sp[16]: Alignment padding, if necessary.
4566  // sp[8]: Preserved x22 (used for argc).
4567  // sp -> sp[0]: Space reserved for the return address.
4568 
4569  // TODO(jgruber): Swap these registers in the calling convention instead.
4570  static_assert(target_input == x1);
4571  static_assert(argv_input == x11);
4572  __ Swap(target_input, argv_input);
4573  static constexpr Register target = x11;
4574  static constexpr Register argv = x1;
4575  static_assert(!AreAliased(argc_input, argc, target, argv));
4576 
4577  // Prepare AAPCS64 arguments to pass to the builtin.
4578  static_assert(argc_input == x0); // Already in the right spot.
4579  static_assert(argv == x1); // Already in the right spot.
4580  __ Mov(x2, ER::isolate_address());
4581 
4582  __ StoreReturnAddressAndCall(target);
4583 
4584  // Result returned in x0 or x1:x0 - do not destroy these registers!
4585 
4586  // x0 result0 The return code from the call.
4587  // x1 result1 For calls which return ObjectPair.
4588  // x22 argc .. only if ArgvMode::kStack.
4589  const Register& result = x0;
4590 
4591  // Check result for exception sentinel.
4592  Label exception_returned;
4593  // The returned value may be a trusted object, living outside of the main
4594  // pointer compression cage, so we need to use full pointer comparison here.
4595  __ CompareRoot(result, RootIndex::kException, ComparisonMode::kFullPointer);
4596  __ B(eq, &exception_returned);
4597 
4598 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4599  if (switch_to_central_stack) {
4600  SwitchFromTheCentralStackIfNeeded(masm);
4601  }
4602 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4603 
4604  // The call succeeded, so unwind the stack and return.
4605  if (argv_mode == ArgvMode::kStack) {
4606  __ Mov(x11, argc); // x11 used as scratch, just til DropArguments below.
4607  __ LeaveExitFrame(x10, x9);
4608  __ DropArguments(x11);
4609  } else {
4610  __ LeaveExitFrame(x10, x9);
4611  }
4612 
4613  __ AssertFPCRState();
4614  __ Ret();
4615 
4616  // Handling of exception.
4617  __ Bind(&exception_returned);
4618 
4619  // Ask the runtime for help to determine the handler. This will set x0 to
4620  // contain the current exception, don't clobber it.
4621  {
4622  FrameScope scope(masm, StackFrame::MANUAL);
4623  __ Mov(x0, 0); // argc.
4624  __ Mov(x1, 0); // argv.
4625  __ Mov(x2, ER::isolate_address());
4626  __ CallCFunction(ER::Create(Runtime::kUnwindAndFindExceptionHandler), 3,
4627  SetIsolateDataSlots::kNo);
4628  }
4629 
4630  // Retrieve the handler context, SP and FP.
4631  __ Mov(cp, ER::Create(IsolateAddressId::kPendingHandlerContextAddress,
4632  masm->isolate()));
4633  __ Ldr(cp, MemOperand(cp));
4634  {
4635  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm);
4636  temps.Exclude(x16);
4637  Register scratch = x1;
4638  __ Mov(scratch, ER::Create(IsolateAddressId::kPendingHandlerSPAddress,
4639  masm->isolate()));
4640  __ Ldr(scratch, MemOperand(scratch));
4641  if (masm->options().enable_simulator_code) {
4642  // Update the simulator stack limit in case the exception was caught in a
4643  // different stack.
4644  __ LoadStackLimit(x16, StackLimitKind::kRealStackLimit);
4645  __ hlt(kImmExceptionIsSwitchStackLimit);
4646  }
4647  __ Mov(sp, scratch);
4648  }
4649  __ Mov(fp, ER::Create(IsolateAddressId::kPendingHandlerFPAddress,
4650  masm->isolate()));
4651  __ Ldr(fp, MemOperand(fp));
4652 
4653  // If the handler is a JS frame, restore the context to the frame. Note that
4654  // the context will be set to (cp == 0) for non-JS frames.
4655  Label not_js_frame;
4656  __ Cbz(cp, &not_js_frame);
4657  __ Str(cp, MemOperand(fp, StandardFrameConstants::kContextOffset));
4658  __ Bind(&not_js_frame);
4659 
4660  {
4661  // Clear c_entry_fp, like we do in `LeaveExitFrame`.
4662  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm);
4663  Register scratch = temps.AcquireX();
4664  __ Mov(scratch,
4665  ER::Create(IsolateAddressId::kCEntryFPAddress, masm->isolate()));
4666  __ Str(xzr, MemOperand(scratch));
4667  }
4668 
4669  // Compute the handler entry address and jump to it. We use x17 here for the
4670  // jump target, as this jump can occasionally end up at the start of
4671  // InterpreterEnterAtBytecode, which when CFI is enabled starts with
4672  // a "BTI c".
4673  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm);
4674  temps.Exclude(x17);
4675  __ Mov(x17, ER::Create(IsolateAddressId::kPendingHandlerEntrypointAddress,
4676  masm->isolate()));
4677  __ Ldr(x17, MemOperand(x17));
4678  __ Br(x17);
4679 }

4682 void Builtins::Generate_WasmHandleStackOverflow(MacroAssembler* masm) {
4683  using ER = ExternalReference;

4687  DCHECK_NE(kCArgRegs[1], frame_base);

4699  }

4727  MemOperand(fp, WasmFrameConstants::kWasmInstanceDataOffset));

4729  cp, FieldMemOperand(kWasmImplicitArgRegister,
4730  WasmTrustedInstanceData::kNativeContextOffset));

4732  __ EnterFrame(StackFrame::INTERNAL);
4733  __ SmiTag(gap);
4734  __ PushArgument(gap);

4742 void Builtins::Generate_DoubleToI(MacroAssembler* masm) {
4743  Label done;
4744  Register result = x7;
4745 
4746  DCHECK(result.Is64Bits());
4747 
4748  HardAbortScope hard_abort(masm); // Avoid calls to Abort.
4749  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm);
4750  Register scratch1 = temps.AcquireX();
4751  Register scratch2 = temps.AcquireX();
4752  DoubleRegister double_scratch = temps.AcquireD();
4753 
4754  // Account for saved regs.
4755  const int kArgumentOffset = 2 * kSystemPointerSize;
4756 
4757  __ Push(result, scratch1); // scratch1 is also pushed to preserve alignment.
4758  __ Peek(double_scratch, kArgumentOffset);
4759 
4760  // Try to convert with a FPU convert instruction. This handles all
4761  // non-saturating cases.
4762  __ TryConvertDoubleToInt64(result, double_scratch, &done);
4763  __ Fmov(result, double_scratch);
4764 
4765  // If we reach here we need to manually convert the input to an int32.
4766 
4767  // Extract the exponent.
4768  Register exponent = scratch1;
4769  __ Ubfx(exponent, result, HeapNumber::kMantissaBits,
4770  HeapNumber::kExponentBits);
4771 
4772  // It the exponent is >= 84 (kMantissaBits + 32), the result is always 0 since
4773  // the mantissa gets shifted completely out of the int32_t result.
4774  __ Cmp(exponent, HeapNumber::kExponentBias + HeapNumber::kMantissaBits + 32);
4775  __ CzeroX(result, ge);
4776  __ B(ge, &done);
4777 
4778  // The Fcvtzs sequence handles all cases except where the conversion causes
4779  // signed overflow in the int64_t target. Since we've already handled
4780  // exponents >= 84, we can guarantee that 63 <= exponent < 84.
4781 
4782  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
4783  __ Cmp(exponent, HeapNumber::kExponentBias + 63);
4784  // Exponents less than this should have been handled by the Fcvt case.
4785  __ Check(ge, AbortReason::kUnexpectedValue);
4786  }
4787 
4788  // Isolate the mantissa bits, and set the implicit '1'.
4789  Register mantissa = scratch2;
4790  __ Ubfx(mantissa, result, 0, HeapNumber::kMantissaBits);
4791  __ Orr(mantissa, mantissa, 1ULL << HeapNumber::kMantissaBits);
4792 
4793  // Negate the mantissa if necessary.
4794  __ Tst(result, kXSignMask);
4795  __ Cneg(mantissa, mantissa, ne);
4796 
4797  // Shift the mantissa bits in the correct place. We know that we have to shift
4798  // it left here, because exponent >= 63 >= kMantissaBits.
4799  __ Sub(exponent, exponent,
4800  HeapNumber::kExponentBias + HeapNumber::kMantissaBits);
4801  __ Lsl(result, mantissa, exponent);
4802 
4803  __ Bind(&done);
4804  __ Poke(result, kArgumentOffset);
4805  __ Pop(scratch1, result);
4806  __ Ret();
4807 }
