4809 void Builtins::Generate_CallApiCallbackImpl(MacroAssembler* masm,
4810  CallApiCallbackMode mode) {
4811  // ----------- S t a t e -------------
4812  // CallApiCallbackMode::kOptimizedNoProfiling/kOptimized modes:
4813  // -- x1 : api function address
4814  // Both modes:
4815  // -- x2 : arguments count (not including the receiver)
4816  // -- x3 : FunctionTemplateInfo
4817  // -- cp : context
4818  // -- sp[0] : receiver
4819  // -- sp[8] : first argument
4820  // -- ...
4821  // -- sp[(argc) * 8] : last argument
4822  // -----------------------------------
4823 
4824  Register function_callback_info_arg = kCArgRegs[0];
4825 
4826  Register api_function_address = no_reg;
4827  Register argc = no_reg;
4828  Register func_templ = no_reg;
4829  Register topmost_script_having_context = no_reg;
4830  Register scratch = x4;
4831 
4832  switch (mode) {
4833  case CallApiCallbackMode::kGeneric:
4834  argc = CallApiCallbackGenericDescriptor::ActualArgumentsCountRegister();
4835  topmost_script_having_context = CallApiCallbackGenericDescriptor::
4836  TopmostScriptHavingContextRegister();
4837  func_templ =
4838  CallApiCallbackGenericDescriptor::FunctionTemplateInfoRegister();
4839  break;
4840 
4841  case CallApiCallbackMode::kOptimizedNoProfiling:
4842  case CallApiCallbackMode::kOptimized:
4843  // Caller context is always equal to current context because we don't
4844  // inline Api calls cross-context.
4845  topmost_script_having_context = kContextRegister;
4846  api_function_address =
4847  CallApiCallbackOptimizedDescriptor::ApiFunctionAddressRegister();
4848  argc = CallApiCallbackOptimizedDescriptor::ActualArgumentsCountRegister();
4849  func_templ =
4850  CallApiCallbackOptimizedDescriptor::FunctionTemplateInfoRegister();
4851  break;
4852  }
4853  DCHECK(!AreAliased(api_function_address, topmost_script_having_context, argc,
4854  func_templ, scratch));
4855 
4856  using FCA = FunctionCallbackArguments;
4857  using ER = ExternalReference;
4858  using FC = ApiCallbackExitFrameConstants;
4859 
4860  static_assert(FCA::kArgsLength == 6);
4861  static_assert(FCA::kNewTargetIndex == 5);
4862  static_assert(FCA::kTargetIndex == 4);
4863  static_assert(FCA::kReturnValueIndex == 3);
4864  static_assert(FCA::kContextIndex == 2);
4865  static_assert(FCA::kIsolateIndex == 1);
4866  static_assert(FCA::kUnusedIndex == 0);
4867 
4868  // Set up FunctionCallbackInfo's implicit_args on the stack as follows:
4869  // Target state:
4870  // sp[0 * kSystemPointerSize]: kUnused <= FCA::implicit_args_
4871  // sp[1 * kSystemPointerSize]: kIsolate
4872  // sp[2 * kSystemPointerSize]: kContext
4873  // sp[3 * kSystemPointerSize]: undefined (kReturnValue)
4874  // sp[4 * kSystemPointerSize]: kTarget
4875  // sp[5 * kSystemPointerSize]: undefined (kNewTarget)
4876  // Existing state:
4877  // sp[6 * kSystemPointerSize]: <= FCA:::values_
4878 
4879  __ StoreRootRelative(IsolateData::topmost_script_having_context_offset(),
4880  topmost_script_having_context);
4881 
4882  if (mode == CallApiCallbackMode::kGeneric) {
4883  api_function_address = ReassignRegister(topmost_script_having_context);
4884  }
4885 
4886  // Reserve space on the stack.
4887  static constexpr int kStackSize = FCA::kArgsLength;
4888  static_assert(kStackSize % 2 == 0);
4889  __ Claim(kStackSize, kSystemPointerSize);
4890 
4891  // kIsolate.
4892  __ Mov(scratch, ER::isolate_address());
4893  __ Str(scratch, MemOperand(sp, FCA::kIsolateIndex * kSystemPointerSize));
4894 
4895  // kContext.
4896  __ Str(cp, MemOperand(sp, FCA::kContextIndex * kSystemPointerSize));
4897 
4898  // kReturnValue.
4899  __ LoadRoot(scratch, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
4900  __ Str(scratch, MemOperand(sp, FCA::kReturnValueIndex * kSystemPointerSize));
4901 
4902  // kTarget.
4903  __ Str(func_templ, MemOperand(sp, FCA::kTargetIndex * kSystemPointerSize));
4904 
4905  // kNewTarget.
4906  __ Str(scratch, MemOperand(sp, FCA::kNewTargetIndex * kSystemPointerSize));
4907 
4908  // kUnused.
4909  __ Str(scratch, MemOperand(sp, FCA::kUnusedIndex * kSystemPointerSize));
4910 
4911  FrameScope frame_scope(masm, StackFrame::MANUAL);
4912  if (mode == CallApiCallbackMode::kGeneric) {
4913  __ LoadExternalPointerField(
4914  api_function_address,
4915  FieldMemOperand(func_templ,
4916  FunctionTemplateInfo::kMaybeRedirectedCallbackOffset),
4917  kFunctionTemplateInfoCallbackTag);
4918  }
4919 
4920  __ EnterExitFrame(scratch, FC::getExtraSlotsCountFrom<ExitFrameConstants>(),
4921  StackFrame::API_CALLBACK_EXIT);
4922 
4923  // This is a workaround for performance regression observed on Apple Silicon
4924  // (https://crbug.com/347741609): reading argc value after the call via
4925  // MemOperand argc_operand = MemOperand(fp, FC::kFCIArgcOffset);
4926  // is noticeably slower than using sp-based access:
4927  MemOperand argc_operand = ExitFrameStackSlotOperand(FCA::kLengthOffset);
4928  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
4929  // Ensure sp-based calculation of FC::length_'s address matches the
4930  // fp-based one.
4931  Label ok;
4932  // +kSystemPointerSize is for the slot at [sp] which is reserved in all
4933  // ExitFrames for storing the return PC.
4934  __ Add(scratch, sp,
4935  FCA::kLengthOffset + kSystemPointerSize - FC::kFCIArgcOffset);
4936  __ cmp(scratch, fp);
4937  __ B(eq, &ok);
4938  __ DebugBreak();
4939  __ Bind(&ok);
4940  }
4941  {
4942  ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(masm, "Initialize v8::FunctionCallbackInfo");
4943  // FunctionCallbackInfo::length_.
4944  // TODO(ishell): pass JSParameterCount(argc) to simplify things on the
4945  // caller end.
4946  __ Str(argc, argc_operand);
4947 
4948  // FunctionCallbackInfo::implicit_args_.
4949  __ Add(scratch, fp, Operand(FC::kImplicitArgsArrayOffset));
4950  __ Str(scratch, MemOperand(fp, FC::kFCIImplicitArgsOffset));
4951 
4952  // FunctionCallbackInfo::values_ (points at JS arguments on the stack).
4953  __ Add(scratch, fp, Operand(FC::kFirstArgumentOffset));
4954  __ Str(scratch, MemOperand(fp, FC::kFCIValuesOffset));
4955  }
4956 
4957  __ RecordComment("v8::FunctionCallback's argument.");
4958  // function_callback_info_arg = v8::FunctionCallbackInfo&
4959  __ Add(function_callback_info_arg, fp,
4960  Operand(FC::kFunctionCallbackInfoOffset));
4961 
4962  DCHECK(!AreAliased(api_function_address, function_callback_info_arg));
4963 
4964  ExternalReference thunk_ref = ER::invoke_function_callback(mode);
4965  Register no_thunk_arg = no_reg;
4966 
4967  MemOperand return_value_operand = MemOperand(fp, FC::kReturnValueOffset);
4968  static constexpr int kSlotsToDropOnReturn =
4969  FC::kFunctionCallbackInfoArgsLength + kJSArgcReceiverSlots;
4970 
4971  const bool with_profiling =
4972  mode != CallApiCallbackMode::kOptimizedNoProfiling;
4973  CallApiFunctionAndReturn(masm, with_profiling, api_function_address,
4974  thunk_ref, no_thunk_arg, kSlotsToDropOnReturn,
4975  &argc_operand, return_value_operand);
4976 }

4978 void Builtins::Generate_CallApiGetter(MacroAssembler* masm) {
4979  // ----------- S t a t e -------------
4980  // -- cp : context
4981  // -- x1 : receiver
4982  // -- x3 : accessor info
4983  // -- x0 : holder
4984  // -----------------------------------
4985 
4986  Register name_arg = kCArgRegs[0];
4987  Register property_callback_info_arg = kCArgRegs[1];
4988 
4989  Register api_function_address = x2;
4990  Register receiver = ApiGetterDescriptor::ReceiverRegister();
4991  Register holder = ApiGetterDescriptor::HolderRegister();
4992  Register callback = ApiGetterDescriptor::CallbackRegister();
4993  Register scratch = x4;
4994  Register undef = x5;
4995  Register scratch2 = x6;
4996 
4997  DCHECK(!AreAliased(receiver, holder, callback, scratch, undef, scratch2));
4998 
4999  // Build v8::PropertyCallbackInfo::args_ array on the stack and push property
5000  // name below the exit frame to make GC aware of them.
5001  using PCA = PropertyCallbackArguments;
5002  using ER = ExternalReference;
5003  using FC = ApiAccessorExitFrameConstants;
5004 
5005  static_assert(PCA::kPropertyKeyIndex == 0);
5006  static_assert(PCA::kShouldThrowOnErrorIndex == 1);
5007  static_assert(PCA::kHolderIndex == 2);
5008  static_assert(PCA::kIsolateIndex == 3);
5009  static_assert(PCA::kHolderV2Index == 4);
5010  static_assert(PCA::kReturnValueIndex == 5);
5011  static_assert(PCA::kDataIndex == 6);
5012  static_assert(PCA::kThisIndex == 7);
5013  static_assert(PCA::kArgsLength == 8);
5014 
5015  // Set up v8::PropertyCallbackInfo's (PCI) args_ on the stack as follows:
5016  // Target state:
5017  // sp[0 * kSystemPointerSize]: name <= PCI::args_
5018  // sp[1 * kSystemPointerSize]: kShouldThrowOnErrorIndex
5019  // sp[2 * kSystemPointerSize]: kHolderIndex
5020  // sp[3 * kSystemPointerSize]: kIsolateIndex
5021  // sp[4 * kSystemPointerSize]: kHolderV2Index
5022  // sp[5 * kSystemPointerSize]: kReturnValueIndex
5023  // sp[6 * kSystemPointerSize]: kDataIndex
5024  // sp[7 * kSystemPointerSize]: kThisIndex / receiver
5025 
5026  __ LoadTaggedField(scratch,
5027  FieldMemOperand(callback, AccessorInfo::kDataOffset));
5028  __ LoadRoot(undef, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
5029  __ Mov(scratch2, ER::isolate_address());
5030  Register holderV2 = xzr;
5031  __ Push(receiver, scratch, // kThisIndex, kDataIndex
5032  undef, holderV2, // kReturnValueIndex, kHolderV2Index
5033  scratch2, holder); // kIsolateIndex, kHolderIndex
5034 
5035  // |name_arg| clashes with |holder|, so we need to push holder first.
5036  __ LoadTaggedField(name_arg,
5037  FieldMemOperand(callback, AccessorInfo::kNameOffset));
5038  static_assert(kDontThrow == 0);
5039  Register should_throw_on_error = xzr; // should_throw_on_error -> kDontThrow
5040  __ Push(should_throw_on_error, name_arg);
5041 
5042  __ RecordComment("Load api_function_address");
5043  __ LoadExternalPointerField(
5044  api_function_address,
5045  FieldMemOperand(callback, AccessorInfo::kMaybeRedirectedGetterOffset),
5046  kAccessorInfoGetterTag);
5047 
5048  FrameScope frame_scope(masm, StackFrame::MANUAL);
5049  __ EnterExitFrame(scratch, FC::getExtraSlotsCountFrom<ExitFrameConstants>(),
5050  StackFrame::API_ACCESSOR_EXIT);
5051 
5052  __ RecordComment("Create v8::PropertyCallbackInfo object on the stack.");
5053  // property_callback_info_arg = v8::PropertyCallbackInfo&
5054  __ Add(property_callback_info_arg, fp, Operand(FC::kArgsArrayOffset));
5055 
5056  DCHECK(!AreAliased(api_function_address, property_callback_info_arg, name_arg,
5057  callback, scratch, scratch2));
5058 
5059 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_DIRECT_HANDLE
5060  // name_arg = Local<Name>(name), name value was pushed to GC-ed stack space.
5061  // |name_arg| is already initialized above.
5062 #else
5063  // name_arg = Local<Name>(&name), which is &args_array[kPropertyKeyIndex].
5064  static_assert(PCA::kPropertyKeyIndex == 0);
5065  __ mov(name_arg, property_callback_info_arg);
5066 #endif
5067 
5068  ExternalReference thunk_ref = ER::invoke_accessor_getter_callback();
5069  // Pass AccessorInfo to thunk wrapper in case profiler or side-effect
5070  // checking is enabled.
5071  Register thunk_arg = callback;
5072 
5073  MemOperand return_value_operand = MemOperand(fp, FC::kReturnValueOffset);
5074  static constexpr int kSlotsToDropOnReturn =
5075  FC::kPropertyCallbackInfoArgsLength;
5076  MemOperand* const kUseStackSpaceConstant = nullptr;
5077 
5078  const bool with_profiling = true;
5079  CallApiFunctionAndReturn(masm, with_profiling, api_function_address,
5080  thunk_ref, thunk_arg, kSlotsToDropOnReturn,
5081  kUseStackSpaceConstant, return_value_operand);

5084 void Builtins::Generate_DirectCEntry(MacroAssembler* masm) {
5085  // The sole purpose of DirectCEntry is for movable callers (e.g. any general
5086  // purpose InstructionStream object) to be able to call into C functions that
5087  // may trigger GC and thus move the caller.
5088  //
5089  // DirectCEntry places the return address on the stack (updated by the GC),
5090  // making the call GC safe. The irregexp backend relies on this.
5091 
5092  __ Poke<MacroAssembler::kSignLR>(lr, 0); // Store the return address.
5093  __ Blr(x10); // Call the C++ function.
5094  __ Peek<MacroAssembler::kAuthLR>(lr, 0); // Return to calling code.
5095  __ AssertFPCRState();
5096  __ Ret();
5097 }

5101 template <typename RegisterT>
5102 void CopyRegListToFrame(MacroAssembler* masm, const Register& dst,
5103  int dst_offset, const CPURegList& reg_list,
5104  const RegisterT& temp0, const RegisterT& temp1,
5105  int src_offset = 0) {
5106  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(masm);
5107  DCHECK_EQ(reg_list.Count() % 2, 0);
5108  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm);
5109  CPURegList copy_to_input = reg_list;
5110  int reg_size = reg_list.RegisterSizeInBytes();
5111  DCHECK_EQ(temp0.SizeInBytes(), reg_size);
5112  DCHECK_EQ(temp1.SizeInBytes(), reg_size);
5113 
5114  // Compute some temporary addresses to avoid having the macro assembler set
5115  // up a temp with an offset for accesses out of the range of the addressing
5116  // mode.
5117  Register src = temps.AcquireX();
5118  masm->Add(src, sp, src_offset);
5119  masm->Add(dst, dst, dst_offset);
5120 
5121  // Write reg_list into the frame pointed to by dst.
5122  for (int i = 0; i < reg_list.Count(); i += 2) {
5123  masm->Ldp(temp0, temp1, MemOperand(src, i * reg_size));
5124 
5125  CPURegister reg0 = copy_to_input.PopLowestIndex();
5126  CPURegister reg1 = copy_to_input.PopLowestIndex();
5127  int offset0 = reg0.code() * reg_size;
5128  int offset1 = reg1.code() * reg_size;
5129 
5130  // Pair up adjacent stores, otherwise write them separately.
5131  if (offset1 == offset0 + reg_size) {
5132  masm->Stp(temp0, temp1, MemOperand(dst, offset0));
5133  } else {
5134  masm->Str(temp0, MemOperand(dst, offset0));
5135  masm->Str(temp1, MemOperand(dst, offset1));
5136  }
5137  }
5138  masm->Sub(dst, dst, dst_offset);
5139 }

5141 void RestoreRegList(MacroAssembler* masm, const CPURegList& reg_list,
5142  const Register& src_base, int src_offset) {
5143  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(masm);
5144  DCHECK_EQ(reg_list.Count() % 2, 0);
5145  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm);
5146  CPURegList restore_list = reg_list;
5147  int reg_size = restore_list.RegisterSizeInBytes();
5148 
5149  // Compute a temporary addresses to avoid having the macro assembler set
5150  // up a temp with an offset for accesses out of the range of the addressing
5151  // mode.
5152  Register src = temps.AcquireX();
5153  masm->Add(src, src_base, src_offset);
5154 
5155  // No need to restore padreg.
5156  restore_list.Remove(padreg);
5157 
5158  // Restore every register in restore_list from src.
5159  while (!restore_list.IsEmpty()) {
5160  CPURegister reg0 = restore_list.PopLowestIndex();
5161  CPURegister reg1 = restore_list.PopLowestIndex();
5162  int offset0 = reg0.code() * reg_size;
5163 
5164  if (reg1 == NoCPUReg) {
5165  masm->Ldr(reg0, MemOperand(src, offset0));
5166  break;
5167  }
5168 
5169  int offset1 = reg1.code() * reg_size;
5170 
5171  // Pair up adjacent loads, otherwise read them separately.
5172  if (offset1 == offset0 + reg_size) {
5173  masm->Ldp(reg0, reg1, MemOperand(src, offset0));
5174  } else {
5175  masm->Ldr(reg0, MemOperand(src, offset0));
5176  masm->Ldr(reg1, MemOperand(src, offset1));
5177  }
5178  }

5181 void Generate_DeoptimizationEntry(MacroAssembler* masm,
5182  DeoptimizeKind deopt_kind) {
5183  Isolate* isolate = masm->isolate();
5184 
5185  // TODO(all): This code needs to be revisited. We probably only need to save
5186  // caller-saved registers here. Callee-saved registers can be stored directly
5187  // in the input frame.
5188 
5189  // Save all allocatable simd128 / double registers.
5190  CPURegList saved_simd128_registers(
5191  kQRegSizeInBits,
5192  DoubleRegList::FromBits(
5193  RegisterConfiguration::Default()->allocatable_simd128_codes_mask()));
5194  DCHECK_EQ(saved_simd128_registers.Count() % 2, 0);
5195  __ PushCPURegList(saved_simd128_registers);
5196 
5197  // We save all the registers except sp, lr, platform register (x18) and the
5198  // masm scratches.
5199  CPURegList saved_registers(CPURegister::kRegister, kXRegSizeInBits, 0, 28);
5200  saved_registers.Remove(ip0);
5201  saved_registers.Remove(ip1);
5202  saved_registers.Remove(x18);
5203  saved_registers.Combine(fp);
5204  saved_registers.Align();
5205  DCHECK_EQ(saved_registers.Count() % 2, 0);
5206  __ PushCPURegList(saved_registers);
5207 
5208  __ Mov(x3, Operand(ExternalReference::Create(
5209  IsolateAddressId::kCEntryFPAddress, isolate)));
5210  __ Str(fp, MemOperand(x3));
5211 
5212  const int kSavedRegistersAreaSize =
5213  (saved_registers.Count() * kXRegSize) +
5214  (saved_simd128_registers.Count() * kQRegSize);
5215 
5216  // Floating point registers are saved on the stack above core registers.
5217  const int kSimd128RegistersOffset = saved_registers.Count() * kXRegSize;
5218 
5219  Register code_object = x2;
5220  Register fp_to_sp = x3;
5221  // Get the address of the location in the code object. This is the return
5222  // address for lazy deoptimization.
5223  __ Mov(code_object, lr);
5224  // Compute the fp-to-sp delta.
5225  __ Add(fp_to_sp, sp, kSavedRegistersAreaSize);
5226  __ Sub(fp_to_sp, fp, fp_to_sp);
5227 
5228  // Allocate a new deoptimizer object.
5229  __ Ldr(x1, MemOperand(fp, CommonFrameConstants::kContextOrFrameTypeOffset));
5230 
5231  // Ensure we can safely load from below fp.
5232  DCHECK_GT(kSavedRegistersAreaSize, -StandardFrameConstants::kFunctionOffset);
5233  __ Ldr(x0, MemOperand(fp, StandardFrameConstants::kFunctionOffset));
5234 
5235  // If x1 is a smi, zero x0.
5236  __ Tst(x1, kSmiTagMask);
5237  __ CzeroX(x0, eq);
5238 
5239  __ Mov(x1, static_cast<int>(deopt_kind));
5240  // Following arguments are already loaded:
5241  // - x2: code object address
5242  // - x3: fp-to-sp delta
5243  __ Mov(x4, ExternalReference::isolate_address());
5244 
5245  {
5246  // Call Deoptimizer::New().
5247  AllowExternalCallThatCantCauseGC scope(masm);
5248  __ CallCFunction(ExternalReference::new_deoptimizer_function(), 5);
5249  }
5250 
5251  // Preserve "deoptimizer" object in register x0.
5252  Register deoptimizer = x0;
5253 
5254  // Get the input frame descriptor pointer.
5255  __ Ldr(x1, MemOperand(deoptimizer, Deoptimizer::input_offset()));
5256 
5257  // Copy core registers into the input frame.
5258  CopyRegListToFrame(masm, x1, FrameDescription::registers_offset(),
5259  saved_registers, x2, x3);
5260 
5261  // Copy simd128 / double registers to the input frame.
5262  CopyRegListToFrame(masm, x1, FrameDescription::simd128_registers_offset(),
5263  saved_simd128_registers, q2, q3, kSimd128RegistersOffset);
5264 
5265  // Mark the stack as not iterable for the CPU profiler which won't be able to
5266  // walk the stack without the return address.
5267  {
5268  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm);
5269  Register is_iterable = temps.AcquireX();
5270  __ LoadIsolateField(is_iterable, IsolateFieldId::kStackIsIterable);
5271  __ strb(xzr, MemOperand(is_iterable));
5272  }
5273 
5274  // Remove the saved registers from the stack.
5275  DCHECK_EQ(kSavedRegistersAreaSize % kXRegSize, 0);
5276  __ Drop(kSavedRegistersAreaSize / kXRegSize);
5277 
5278  // Compute a pointer to the unwinding limit in register x2; that is
5279  // the first stack slot not part of the input frame.
5280  Register unwind_limit = x2;
5281  __ Ldr(unwind_limit, MemOperand(x1, FrameDescription::frame_size_offset()));
5282 
5283  // Unwind the stack down to - but not including - the unwinding
5284  // limit and copy the contents of the activation frame to the input
5285  // frame description.
5286  __ Add(x3, x1, FrameDescription::frame_content_offset());
5287  __ SlotAddress(x1, 0);
5288  __ Lsr(unwind_limit, unwind_limit, kSystemPointerSizeLog2);
5289  __ Mov(x5, unwind_limit);
5290  __ CopyDoubleWords(x3, x1, x5);
5291  // Since {unwind_limit} is the frame size up to the parameter count, we might
5292  // end up with an unaligned stack pointer. This is later recovered when
5293  // setting the stack pointer to {caller_frame_top_offset}.
5294  __ Bic(unwind_limit, unwind_limit, 1);
5295  __ Drop(unwind_limit);
5296 
5297  // Compute the output frame in the deoptimizer.
5298  __ Push(padreg, x0); // Preserve deoptimizer object across call.
5299  {
5300  // Call Deoptimizer::ComputeOutputFrames().
5301  AllowExternalCallThatCantCauseGC scope(masm);
5302  __ CallCFunction(ExternalReference::compute_output_frames_function(), 1);
5303  }
5304  __ Pop(x4, padreg); // Restore deoptimizer object (class Deoptimizer).
5305 
5306  {
5307  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm);
5308  Register scratch = temps.AcquireX();
5309  __ Ldr(scratch, MemOperand(x4, Deoptimizer::caller_frame_top_offset()));
5310  __ Mov(sp, scratch);
5311  }
5312 
5313  // Replace the current (input) frame with the output frames.
5314  Label outer_push_loop, outer_loop_header;
5315  __ Ldrsw(x1, MemOperand(x4, Deoptimizer::output_count_offset()));
5316  __ Ldr(x0, MemOperand(x4, Deoptimizer::output_offset()));
5317  __ Add(x1, x0, Operand(x1, LSL, kSystemPointerSizeLog2));
5318  __ B(&outer_loop_header);
5319 
5320  __ Bind(&outer_push_loop);
5321  Register current_frame = x2;
5322  Register frame_size = x3;
5323  __ Ldr(current_frame, MemOperand(x0, kSystemPointerSize, PostIndex));
5324  __ Ldr(x3, MemOperand(current_frame, FrameDescription::frame_size_offset()));
5325  __ Lsr(frame_size, x3, kSystemPointerSizeLog2);
5326  __ Claim(frame_size, kXRegSize, /*assume_sp_aligned=*/false);
5327 
5328  __ Add(x7, current_frame, FrameDescription::frame_content_offset());
5329  __ SlotAddress(x6, 0);
5330  __ CopyDoubleWords(x6, x7, frame_size);
5331 
5332  __ Bind(&outer_loop_header);
5333  __ Cmp(x0, x1);
5334  __ B(lt, &outer_push_loop);
5335 
5336  RestoreRegList(masm, saved_simd128_registers, current_frame,
5337  FrameDescription::simd128_registers_offset());
5338 
5339  {
5340  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm);
5341  Register is_iterable = temps.AcquireX();
5342  Register one = x4;
5343  __ LoadIsolateField(is_iterable, IsolateFieldId::kStackIsIterable);
5344  __ Mov(one, Operand(1));
5345  __ strb(one, MemOperand(is_iterable));
5346  }
5347 
5348  // TODO(all): ARM copies a lot (if not all) of the last output frame onto the
5349  // stack, then pops it all into registers. Here, we try to load it directly
5350  // into the relevant registers. Is this correct? If so, we should improve the
5351  // ARM code.
5352 
5353  // Restore registers from the last output frame.
5354  // Note that lr is not in the list of saved_registers and will be restored
5355  // later. We can use it to hold the address of last output frame while
5356  // reloading the other registers.
5357  DCHECK(!saved_registers.IncludesAliasOf(lr));
5358  Register last_output_frame = lr;
5359  __ Mov(last_output_frame, current_frame);
5360 
5361  RestoreRegList(masm, saved_registers, last_output_frame,
5362  FrameDescription::registers_offset());
5363 
5364  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm);
5365  temps.Exclude(x17);
5366  Register continuation = x17;
5367  __ Ldr(continuation, MemOperand(last_output_frame,
5368  FrameDescription::continuation_offset()));
5369  __ Ldr(lr, MemOperand(last_output_frame, FrameDescription::pc_offset()));
5370 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CONTROL_FLOW_INTEGRITY
5371  __ Autibsp();
5372 #endif
5373  // If the continuation is non-zero (JavaScript), branch to the continuation.
5374  // For Wasm just return to the pc from the last output frame in the lr
5375  // register.
5376  Label end;
5377  __ CompareAndBranch(continuation, 0, eq, &end);
5378  __ Br(continuation);
5379  __ Bind(&end);
5380  __ Ret();
5381 }

5393 void Builtins::Generate_DeoptimizationEntry_LazyAfterFastCall(
5394  MacroAssembler* masm) {
5395  // The deoptimizer may have been triggered right after the return of a fast
5396  // API call. In that case, exception handling and possible stack unwinding
5397  // did not happen yet.
5398  // We check here if a there is a pending exception by comparing the
5399  // exception stored in the isolate with the no-exception sentinel
5400  // (the_hole_value). If there is an exception, we call PropagateException to
5401  // trigger stack unwinding.
5402  Label no_exception;
5403  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm);
5404  Register scratch = temps.AcquireX();
5405  __ Ldr(scratch, __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
5406  ExternalReference::Create(
5407  IsolateAddressId::kExceptionAddress, __ isolate()),
5408  scratch));
5409  __ CompareRoot(scratch, RootIndex::kTheHoleValue);
5410  __ B(eq, &no_exception);
5411 
5412  __ EnterFrame(StackFrame::INTERNAL);
5413  const RegList kCalleeSaveRegisters = {C_CALL_CALLEE_SAVE_REGISTERS};
5414  const DoubleRegList kCalleeSaveFPRegisters = {
5415  C_CALL_CALLEE_SAVE_FP_REGISTERS};
5416  // DeoptimizeEntry_Lazy uses the `lr` register to determine where the deopt
5417  // came from. The runtime call below overwrites the `lr` register. We have to
5418  // spill it on the stack here to preserve it.
5419  __ PushAll(kCalleeSaveFPRegisters);
5420  __ PushAll(kCalleeSaveRegisters);
5421  __ Mov(kContextRegister, Operand(Context::kNoContext));
5422  // We have to reset IsolateData::fast_c_call_caller_fp(), because otherwise
5423  // the stack unwinder thinks that we are still within the fast C call.
5424  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
5425  __ Ldr(scratch,
5426  __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kFastCCallCallerFP));
5427  __ Cmp(scratch, 0);
5428  __ Assert(ne, AbortReason::kFastCallFallbackInvalid);
5429  }
5430  __ Mov(scratch, 0);
5431  __ Str(scratch,
5432  __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kFastCCallCallerFP));
5433  __ CallRuntime(Runtime::FunctionId::kPropagateException);
5434  __ bti(BranchTargetIdentifier::kBtiCall);
5435  __ PopAll(kCalleeSaveRegisters);
5436  __ PopAll(kCalleeSaveFPRegisters);
5437  __ LeaveFrame(StackFrame::INTERNAL);
5438  __ bind(&no_exception);
5439  // Deoptimization expects that the return value of the API call is in the
5440  // return register. As we only allow deoptimization if the return type is
5441  // void, the return value is always `undefined`.
5442  // TODO(crbug.com/418936518): Handle the return value in an actual
5443  // deoptimization continuation.
5444  __ LoadRoot(kReturnRegister0, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
5445  __ TailCallBuiltin(Builtin::kDeoptimizationEntry_Lazy);
5446 }
